column13: Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!|On Friday, March 15 and Saturday, March 16, Austin’s Eye in the Sky Collective and Chicago app startup eevzdrop will take over Shiner’s Saloon in the heart of downtown Austin for the third annual Future of Music Showcase, an unofficial party happening during SXSW presented in partnership with T. Cannon Media, Ditto Music, ATX Music Mag, and Push Music. Food and drink will be provided. Featuring 25+ bands playing from noon-2am each day, this year’s lineup highlights rising Texas stars like Shakey Graves and The Tontons with a selectively curated mix of acts ranging from Chicago hip-hop to Danish psychedelic folk. It will also feature a special performance from the legendary BP Fallon and the Bandits (Third Man Records), featuring Rock and Roll Hall of Famers Scott Asheton (The Stooges), Clem Burke (Blondie), and Nigel Harrison (Blondie). More headliners will be announced in the coming weeks. See below for a list of confirmed acts so far. Curated by Eye in The Sky co-founder and “Vision Quest Executive” Anthony Erickson, The Future of Music Showcase has become a bellwether for predicting SXSW’s next breakout artists. Previous performers have since performed on Jimmy Kimmel Live and Anthony Bourdain’s “No Reservations,” been featured on MTV’s “Buzzworthy” and NPR Music and topped the popularity lists of Hype Machine and Reddit. For a preview of 2013’s artists, stream The Future of Music artist sampler here: https://soundcloud.com/eyeintheskycollective/sets/future-of-music-showcase-2013/s-jX01K

RSVP for FREE on Do512 for Day Two, Day Three and Day Four of MidCoast Takeover 2013


The Midwest Music Foundation is proud to present the fourth annual MidCoast Takeover, March 13th – 16th at Shangri-La in Austin, TX.


This event promises four days of music, mayhem, and general debauchery — the definitive Midwestern musical throw down. MidCoast Takeover will showcase bands from Kansas City, Lawrence, and the Midwest region on the national stage during South by Southwest.

For more information visit: www.midcoasttakeover.com

column14:
THE OUTLAW ROADSHOW is produced by Ryan Spaulding (Creator of rslblog.com and Producer and Host of The Bubbler on myTV38 in New England) and Adam Duritz (of Counting Crows and Producer of the new comedy Freeloaders). The Outlaw returns to Austin, TX this March for 2 SHOWS... Sat, March 9th and Sat, March 16th in Downtown Austin at Rusty's - the best live music venue in the city.

THE OUTLAW ROADSHOW is a thrill ride for the music fan: 3 stages featuring bright emerging bands who deserve some time in your headphones in 2013.

SATURDAY MARCH 16
NOON - Rusty's at 405 East 7th
Austin, TX

NO BADGES REQUIRED

FREE RSVP TO ATTEND!
19 LIVE BANDS


Both sessions of The Outlaw Roadshow 2013 are presented by ZAZOO. Zazoo has introduced a revolutionary new web application that embeds an artist's unique ‘Mini App’ onto each music video, wherever it is watched. Zazoo provides fans with a live, engaging viewing experience – sing along, play along, access lyrics, peak backstage, get special offers and interact with artists who can now reach the broadest audience possible and gain an edge in a fiercely competitive market.

Last year's showcase was attended by thousands and this year we expect the same. Our foremost concern is that everyone is enriched by this process. That means the bands, the fans, the venue, the sound people - in the hope that we'll be able to do this for years to come. The Outlaw Roadshow is all about music and you.


ADDITIONAL EVENT DETAILS
EVENT HISTORY
BUNCH OF OTHER STUFF

* Legal ID and 21+
Admittance requires Free RSVP.
Venue is limited to legal capacity.

column14:
THE OUTLAW ROADSHOW is produced by Ryan Spaulding (Creator of rslblog.com and Producer and Host of The Bubbler on myTV38 in New England) and Adam Duritz (of Counting Crows and Producer of the new comedy Freeloaders). The Outlaw returns to Austin, TX this March for 2 SHOWS... Sat, March 9th and Sat, March 16th in Downtown Austin at Rusty's - the best live music venue in the city.

THE OUTLAW ROADSHOW is a thrill ride for the music fan: 3 stages featuring bright emerging bands who deserve some time in your headphones in 2013.

SATURDAY MARCH 9
8pm - Rusty's at 405 East 7th
Austin, TX

NO BADGES REQUIRED*

FREE RSVP TO ATTEND!
17 LIVE BANDS


Both sessions of The Outlaw Roadshow 2013 are presented by ZAZOO. Zazoo has introduced a revolutionary new web application that embeds an artist's unique ‘Mini App’ onto each music video, wherever it is watched. Zazoo provides fans with a live, engaging viewing experience – sing along, play along, access lyrics, peak backstage, get special offers and interact with artists who can now reach the broadest audience possible and gain an edge in a fiercely competitive market.

Last year's showcase was attended by thousands and this year we expect the same. Our foremost concern is that everyone is enriched by this process. That means the bands, the fans, the venue, the sound people - in the hope that we'll be able to do this for years to come. The Outlaw Roadshow is all about music and you.

ADDITIONAL EVENT DETAILS
EVENT HISTORY
BUNCH OF OTHER STUFF


* Legal ID and 21+
Admittance requires Free RSVP.
Venue is limited to legal capacity.

Click HERE or the image below to submit your entry to play the 9th Annual All Together Now Showcase



RSVP does not guarantee entry, so arrive early!


Welcome to the 9th annual All Together Now Showcase in Austin, TX from March 13-18, 2013. We'll be featuring 60+ bands over 5 days and have already started working on some amazing things for the event!

We at the ATN Showcase always feature an impacting and active charity in our events. We are in the process of researching and finding the absolute best fit for 2013. We are definitely open to any ideas or suggestions. If you would like to submit ideas, please send those to jennifer@atnmanagement.com.

For interview requests, press inquiries, etc. click here.

ATN Management is a hands-on, independent management firm producing charity-driven showcases for the past 7 years. Jennifer DaRe is ATN Management's principle, overseeing the coordination of the All Together Now Showcase.

Jennifer has collected 25 combined years of experience in the music industry and entertainment industry, and 8 years in talent management. Ms. DaRe has amassed a network of industry contacts with whom she has collaborated in developing and growing ATN Management and is well known for her well-rounded and proven managerial style unique in the industry.

Line-up coming soon....

They became foster parents in 1992 and it was through this experience that Ray realized these youth needed more positive opportunities to help them grow into productive citizens. Ray was a life long musician; he knew the benefits of engaging in a music program and he saw few music opportunities for these youth.|He decided to start a music program for foster kids; any child that had the desire would be provided a guitar and free lessons. On July 24, 2000 Guitars not Guns was incorporated and became a federally exempt 501(c) (3) non-profit. Shortly thereafter they started their first guitar class with two volunteer teachers in San Jose, California. Over the next few years classes expanded to neighboring Counties in California and the program expanded to include any youth living in adverse circumstances who lacked the means to participate in a music program. In 2006 the program started spreading outside of California; today GnG’s Music Program is operating in several states and Canada.|Guitars not Guns Virginia was chartered as a GnG Affiliate in June 2006; Guitars not Guns Maryland and Guitars not Guns Washington D.C. were chartered as GnG Affiliates in April 2009. Virginia, Maryland and DC operate jointly asGnG NCA (Guitars Not Guns of the National Capital Area). Collectively we operate 32 teaching locations and serve over 300 youth annually. New locations are being opened as volunteers and funds are found to operate them.|More (delicious and sweet) details to follow soon.|+ in.sessions w/ in.gredients (@ store!)|http://www.in.gredients.com/|http://in.gredients.com/in-sessions/ |(the in.sessions are really special!!!)

HISTORY OF GNG 501(c)3
www.guitarsnotguns.org

“Guitars not Guns” (GnG) was founded by Ray and Louise Nelson. They became foster parents in 1992 and it was through this experience that Ray realized these youth needed more positive opportunities to help them grow into productive citizens. Ray was a life long musician; he knew the benefits of engaging in a music program and he saw few music opportunities for these youth.

He decided to start a music program for foster kids; any child that had the desire would be provided a guitar and free lessons. On July 24, 2000 Guitars not Guns was incorporated and became a federally exempt 501(c) (3) non-profit. Shortly thereafter they started their first guitar class with two volunteer teachers in San Jose, California. Over the next few years classes expanded to neighboring Counties in California and the program expanded to include any youth living in adverse circumstances who lacked the means to participate in a music program. In 2006 the program started spreading outside of California; today GnG’s Music Program is operating in several states and Canada.

Guitars not Guns Virginia was chartered as a GnG Affiliate in June 2006; Guitars not Guns Maryland and Guitars not Guns Washington D.C. were chartered as GnG Affiliates in April 2009. Virginia, Maryland and DC operate jointly asGnG NCA (Guitars Not Guns of the National Capital Area). Collectively we operate 32 teaching locations and serve over 300 youth annually. New locations are being opened as volunteers and funds are found to operate them.

This event promises four days of music, mayhem, and general debauchery — the definitive Midwestern musical throw down. MidCoast Takeover will showcase bands from Kansas City, Lawrence, and the Midwest region on the national stage during South by Southwest.

For more information visit: www.midcoasttakeover.com

column14:
Sponsored in part by Underground Connections, URBANEARS, That Knock, Mindzai Creative, Austin Silent Disco, Evidence Entertainment, CollabNArt, Thumbtack Press & Do512!

-The largest gathering of live art murals in Texas

-The cultivation of one of largest outdoor galleries in the USA

- A massive collaborative gathering celebrating sophisticated urban & contemporary art from around the world.


THE BREAKDOWN
This one of a kind art event will focus on cultivating the HOPE Outdoor Gallery, a massive three-story-tall outdoor urban space that has emerged into one of the largest outdoor galleries in the country.

ReCREATE will include
- Over 50 Artists from around the globe
- Wireless headphone DJ music sets & arts education
- Breakdance Showcases
- ONE GIANT BUS SHUTTLE from downtown to the murals!
- Children’s Painting & Learning Center
- Austin City Photo Booth
- Prizes and Giveaways

OUR MISSION
Our collaborative mission is to encourage global community empowerment through artistic action and education.

To unite artists with the world.
To inspire the uninspired.
To educate future generations about the power of art!

MUCH LOVE TO OUR SPONSORS AND PARTNERS
This event would not be possible without our countless volunteers, sponsors and partners. We thank you from the depths of our hearts ♥

The HOG is brought to the community by Castle Hill Partners, Dick Clark Architecture, Jerry’s Art-O-Rama & the HOPE Campaign

Austin: We have a festival every other weekend. Everyone's got at least one tattoo. For a while we had our own town transvestite. "Keep Austin Weird"? It's Weird Enough! So come over and take your weird out at, March 12th! Pre-show at 8, Comedians at 9! We have a stellar list of local comics!

HOST: Luis Flandes

Rob Gagnon
Pat Sirois
Chance Royce
Michael Navarette
Lawson Bennett
Ben Cholok
Tyler Harris
Eric Nagurney
Jacob Collings

The best part is that it's totally FREE (but donations accepted and much appreciated) and BYOB, sponsored by EZ Irie One Love, merch available.

Do you have a weird talent skill? Would you like to perform that skill to during the Preshow if it will get you free beers for the night? If so, email me at Luisiflandes@gmail.com and we'll see if if I can get you on, I'll take the best 5.

8pm The Dry Season (Austin, TX)

Sponsored by Sweet Tea Pumpkin Pie (STPP)
www.sweetteapumpkinpie.com
www.stppfest.com



HISTORY OF GNG 501(c)3
www.guitarsnotguns.org

“Guitars not Guns” (GnG) was founded by Ray and Louise Nelson. They became foster parents in 1992 and it was through this experience that Ray realized these youth needed more positive opportunities to help them grow into productive citizens. Ray was a life long musician; he knew the benefits of engaging in a music program and he saw few music opportunities for these youth.

He decided to start a music program for foster kids; any child that had the desire would be provided a guitar and free lessons. On July 24, 2000 Guitars not Guns was incorporated and became a federally exempt 501(c) (3) non-profit. Shortly thereafter they started their first guitar class with two volunteer teachers in San Jose, California. Over the next few years classes expanded to neighboring Counties in California and the program expanded to include any youth living in adverse circumstances who lacked the means to participate in a music program. In 2006 the program started spreading outside of California; today GnG’s Music Program is operating in several states and Canada.

Guitars not Guns Virginia was chartered as a GnG Affiliate in June 2006; Guitars not Guns Maryland and Guitars not Guns Washington D.C. were chartered as GnG Affiliates in April 2009. Virginia, Maryland and DC operate jointly asGnG NCA (Guitars Not Guns of the National Capital Area). Collectively we operate 32 teaching locations and serve over 300 youth annually. New locations are being opened as volunteers and funds are found to operate them.

More (delicious and sweet) details to follow soon.

Don't Miss The 31st Annual Austin Music Awards!

TICKETS: On sale at austinchronicle.ticketbud.com and at Waterloo Records on February 21st. $15 in advance, $20 night of show. SXSW badges and wristbands include entry to the show at the Austin Music Hall.

LINE-UP:Confirmed acts include Ben Kweller, The Trishas, Bill Carter. Rest of Line-Up TBD.

Join The Austin Chronicle in celebrating 31 years of Austin music right here in the Live Music Capital! Votes from this year’s Austin Chronicle Music Poll are being tabulated, and the winners will be announced at the 31st Annual Austin Music Awards at 7:09pm SHARP on Wednesday, March 13, at the Austin Music Hall.


In recent years, the Music Awards has seen guest and unannounced appearances from The Who’s PETE TOWNSHEND, Texas favorite son LYLE LOVETT, the mighty KRIS KRISTOFFERSON, and The Boss himself, BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN. With more performers to be announced, expect more surprises!

The Austin Music Awards are presented by The Austin Chronicle and SXSW and co-sponsored by KUTX, Planet K, Discount Electronics, Ticketbud and is a benefit for the SIMS Foundation. This year, the Music Awards show will air live on America’s longest, continually running community television station, channelAustin (Channel 10).


The Austin Chronicle celebrates 32 years as Austin's independent news source, covering music, film, arts, and politics, with 195,000 readers per week in the greater Austin metropolitan area. The Chronicle is the eloquent and incisive voice of the city, expressing the community’s political and environmental concerns and supporting its active cultural scene. The Austin Chronicle is available at over 1,800 locations every Thursday. For more information, go to www.austinchronicle.com.

column14:
Artist rumored. Will update with details as they arise.

Via Justin Timberlake's Open Letter

This year is an exciting one for me. As you probably have heard through the "grapevine," I'm gearing up for a big 2013.


Back in June of last year, I quietly started working on what is now, my next journey with that thing I love called MUSIC.


The inspiration for this really came out of the blue and to be honest, I didn't expect anything out of it. I just went into the studio and started playing around with some sounds and songs. It was probably the best time I've had in my career... Just creating with no rules and/or end goal in mind and really enjoying the process.


What I came up with is something I couldn't be more excited about! It is full of inspiration that I grew up listening to and some newfound muses that I've discovered along the way.

I'm calling it "The 20/20 Experience," and it's coming out this year.


I hope you enjoy listening to it as much as I enjoyed making it.


That's all I'm giving you for now... I know, I know! Again, with the teasing!!!

Get ready. This is going to be fun (well, at least it is for me).

column2: SPIN Magazine Party 2013 (Badges/Wristbands Required) - Kendrick Lamar & More!
column12: Kendrick Lamar
column13: At around this time last year, Compton's Kendrick Lamar was just another underground rapper with potential and a forthcoming major-label debut. Fast forward to today and he may be hip-hop's brightest star — an accomplished, moving storyteller whose good kid, m.A.A.d city flaunted the industry by proving that there's still no formula to pop success. The album topped many critics’ lists in 2012 and is nudging up against platinum certification while appealing equally to teens sculpting the zeitgeist and old heads who haven't touched a radio dial in 15 years.|On Friday, March 15, Lamar will bring his spotlight to Austin, Texas, where he'll headline our annual musical bacchanal at the legendarily finger-lickin' Stubb's BBQ. We'll reveal the rest of the lineup soon, along with info about how you can win the chance to attend this historic throwdown! Follow @spinsxsw for details, and stay tuned for our fest preview and free mixtape!|Via Spin.com
column14:
At around this time last year, Compton's Kendrick Lamar was just another underground rapper with potential and a forthcoming major-label debut. Fast forward to today and he may be hip-hop's brightest star — an accomplished, moving storyteller whose good kid, m.A.A.d city flaunted the industry by proving that there's still no formula to pop success. The album topped many critics’ lists in 2012 and is nudging up against platinum certification while appealing equally to teens sculpting the zeitgeist and old heads who haven't touched a radio dial in 15 years.



On Friday, March 15, Lamar will bring his spotlight to Austin, Texas, where he'll headline our annual musical bacchanal at the legendarily finger-lickin' Stubb's BBQ. We'll reveal the rest of the lineup soon, along with info about how you can win the chance to attend this historic throwdown! Follow @spinsxsw for details, and stay tuned for our fest preview and free mixtape!


Via Spin.com

column14:
Tickets on sale November 30th @ 10:00AM


Rock ‘n’ roll legend Eric Clapton will headline a concert at the Frank Erwin Center Sunday, March 17 with special guest The Wallflowers. The stop in Austin will be Clapton’s only appearance in the area.

Clapton is the only three-time inductee into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame, has won 17 Grammy awards and placed second on Rolling Stone’s list of the “100 Greatest Guitarists of All Time” last year. This will be Clapton’s third concert at the Frank Erwin Center and the first in almost 18 years.

Clapton has assembled an impressive band for the U.S. dates, which will consist of long-time touring partners Doyle Bramhall II (guitar), Steve Jordan (drums), Chris Stainton (piano and keyboards) and Willie Weeks (bass), along with newcomers Paul Carrack (organ and keyboards) and Greg Leisz (pedal steel guitar). Michelle John and Sharon White will join the touring band again as backing vocalists.

column2: Guitartown/Conqueroo in conjunction with M Music and Musicians and AllMusic Present Kickoff 2013
column12: Billy Joe Shaver,Steve Poltz,Tom Freund,Willie Nile,Chris Stamey,Shoes,The Trishas,Nakia,Dash Rip Rock,Michael Des Barres,The Silos,Taylor Greenwood,White Buffalo,Henry Wagons,Chuck Mead & His Grassy Knoll Boys,Jon Dee Graham,American Aquarium,The Waterboys,Howlin' Brothers,James McMurtry,SHURMAN,Chelle Rose,Dustin Welch,Tim Easton,Anne McCue,Charlie Terrell & the Murdered Johns
column13: The 13th annual Guitartown/Conqueroo Kickoff event in conjunction with M Music & Musicians Magazine and AllMusic expands the scope from one venue to two adjacent West 6th Street venues — the Dogwood and Molotov. The expansion brings three stages and a record 29 artists on the bill. Guitartown/Conqueroo happens Wed., March 13, 11 a.m. - 9 p.m. And while the show has always showcased an eclectic mix of high-profile and emerging artists, we may have outdone ourselves this year: Mike Scott and Steve Wickham of the Waterboys open their US. tour here. Legendary Zion, Ill. powerpop band Shoes makes their first foray out of the Midwest in 18 years. Chris Stamey of The dB’s gives a glimpse of his new Yep Roc CD. Billy Joe Shaver performs classics and new songs from his fall 2013 studio album. And that’s just the start: Chuck Mead, Henry Wagons, Chelle Rose, Willie Nile, Nakia, James McMurtry, Michael Des Barres, The Trishas, Dustin Welch, Howlin’ Brothers, Dash Riprock, Steve Poltz, Shurman, the Silos, Tom Freund. Best of all, the event is free and open to the public — no badges. Three full bars to satisfy your thirst and a food menu. Tastemakers, journalists, a&r reps, managers, agents and just plain fans have come to make this they obligatory Wednesday stop during SXSW week. Many come for a particular artist and end up staying well into the night. We hope we’ll see you. Watch for updates at http://on.fb.me/11lDsw5>.

A huge highlight of the evening will be folk rocking powerhouse Lissie, who blew audiences away with her version of Kid Cudi's Pursuit of Happinessduring her performances at SXSW 2012. She comes this year to support the release of her highly anticipated, second full-length album, dropping this summer. This year's annual awards show and festival held by MTV's college network, mtvU, will return to Austin, Texas, for one day of performances from up-and-coming artists during South by Southwest Music Festival beginning at 2 p.m. CST on Thursday, March 14, The Hollywood Reporter has learned exclusively. The ninth annual mtvU Woodie Awards will take place 8 p.m. CST that night.

-- via the Hollywood Reporter

A Mid West Festival + Unofficial Showcase Event during SX in Austin, TX March 12th - 17th, 2013.

This is an Unofficial SXSW Event and brought to you by BSHR Entertainment and Sponsored by Music Saves Lives


THE VENUE

The Firehouse Lounge features classically prepared cocktails, delectable accompaniments, an inviting atmosphere, and a variety of live music. Elevate your experience at Downtown's NEWEST venue.


FEATURING. . .

The giftbags will be given out at the VIP Dinner Party and the Main Event. Mini Moo Business Cards will contain download codes for guests to return home and enter for more goodies!


Plus play the Indie Band Drinking Game + Sky Scavenger Hunt all week to win Sponsored Prize Packages!

THE [SOS] SCHEDULE of SHOWS

Tuesday 3/12 Welcome to Austin: A Singer/Songwriter Party + Evening Events


Wednesday 3/13 Rockin’ Zombie Luau Day Party + Evening Events


Thursday 3/14 The Calm Before the Storm Day Party and the VIP Dinner + Cocktail Party+ evening events.

Mini spa treatments, an art gala with VIP Dinner + Cocktail party.

Friday 3/15 Blue Sky on Broadway + The Indie Dance Party: Bring on the Weekend

The start of the Vinyl Record Club in Partnership with Broadway Recording Company.


Saturday 3/16 BSHR’s “Giant” Launch Party

The main event complete with miniature EVERYTHING. Guests receive The “Grow it @ Home” Giftbag. Raffles of various prizes and giveaways.


Sunday 3/17 The Green Giant Party + Closing events

column2: SouthBites - Gourmet Food Trucks Curated by Paul Qui
column6: 500 East Cesar Chavez Street, Austin, TX, 78701
column13: We are excited to announce that local food maven, Paul Qui is partnering with SXSW to curate a selection of gourmet food trucks for SXSW attendees this year. Paul is the executive Chef at Qui, opening in Spring 2013, the owner of Austin’s renowned East Side King trailers, winner of Top Chef Season 9, and is the recipient of the James Beard Award for Best Chef: Southwest 2012.|SouthBites is operating for all nine days of SXSW (March 8-16), open to the public and located right across the road from the Austin Convention Center. It will be an essential destination for thousands of hungry Music, Film and Interactive fans and industry players.|With Qui’s involvement, SXSW aims to provide a unique, high caliber selection of eateries– bringing together Austin’s well-known food truck culture and diverse range of cuisines.
column14:
We are excited to announce that local food maven, Paul Qui is partnering with SXSW to curate a selection of gourmet food trucks for SXSW attendees this year. Paul is the executive Chef at Qui, opening in Spring 2013, the owner of Austin’s renowned East Side King trailers, winner of Top Chef Season 9, and is the recipient of the James Beard Award for Best Chef: Southwest 2012.


SouthBites is operating for all nine days of SXSW (March 8-16), open to the public and located right across the road from the Austin Convention Center. It will be an essential destination for thousands of hungry Music, Film and Interactive fans and industry players.


With Qui’s involvement, SXSW aims to provide a unique, high caliber selection of eateries– bringing together Austin’s well-known food truck culture and diverse range of cuisines.

column14:
Join us for the Twangfest and KDHX SX Day Parties at the Broken Spoke in Austin. Dates are Thursday, March 14 and Saturday, March 16, noon-5 p.m. each day.

Now in their 14th year, the Twangfest day parties are among the most anticipated afternoon events during the week-long South By Southwest gathering. These parties are open to the public, with RSVP required.

The lineup for the 2013 parties features 18 national artists from a wide-range of twangy genres.

Confirmed Artists:

Kelly Hogan
Bruce Robison & Kelly Willis
Deano and the Purvs
Mount Moriah
Waco Brothers
Whitehorse
Pokey LaFarge and the South City Three
JC Brooks & the Uptown Sound

Full schedule and times coming soon.

RSVP on the Facebook Event page. You may also RSVP by email: sxsw@twangfest.com. Each RSVP may bring up to three guests.

See you in Austin!

column14:
Join us for the Twangfest and KDHX SX Day Parties at the Broken Spoke in Austin. Dates are Thursday, March 14 and Saturday, March 16, noon-5 p.m. each day.

Now in their 14th year, the Twangfest day parties are among the most anticipated afternoon events during the week-long South By Southwest gathering. These parties are open to the public, with RSVP required.

The lineup for the 2013 parties features 18 national artists from a wide-range of twangy genres.

Confirmed Artists:

Kelly Hogan
Bruce Robison & Kelly Willis
Deano and the Purvs
Mount Moriah
Waco Brothers
Whitehorse
Pokey LaFarge and the South City Three
JC Brooks & the Uptown Sound

Full schedule and times coming soon.

RSVP on the Facebook Event page. You may also RSVP by email: sxsw@twangfest.com. Each RSVP may bring up to three guests.

See you in Austin!

column14:
A Mid West Festival + Unofficial Showcase Event during SX in Austin, TX March 12th - 17th, 2013.

This is an Unofficial SXSW Event and brought to you by BSHR Entertainment and Sponsored by Music Saves Lives


THE VENUE

The Firehouse Lounge features classically prepared cocktails, delectable accompaniments, an inviting atmosphere, and a variety of live music. Elevate your experience at Downtown's NEWEST venue.


FEATURING. . .

The giftbags will be given out at the VIP Dinner Party and the Main Event. Mini Moo Business Cards will contain download codes for guests to return home and enter for more goodies!


Plus play the Indie Band Drinking Game + Sky Scavenger Hunt all week to win Sponsored Prize Packages!

THE [SOS] SCHEDULE of SHOWS

Tuesday 3/12 Welcome to Austin: A Singer/Songwriter Party + Evening Events


Wednesday 3/13 Rockin’ Zombie Luau Day Party + Evening Events


Thursday 3/14 The Calm Before the Storm Day Party and the VIP Dinner + Cocktail Party+ evening events.

Mini spa treatments, an art gala with VIP Dinner + Cocktail party.

Friday 3/15 Blue Sky on Broadway + The Indie Dance Party: Bring on the Weekend

The start of the Vinyl Record Club in Partnership with Broadway Recording Company.


Saturday 3/16 BSHR’s “Giant” Launch Party

The main event complete with miniature EVERYTHING. Guests receive The “Grow it @ Home” Giftbag. Raffles of various prizes and giveaways.


Sunday 3/17 The Green Giant Party + Closing events

column2: Music You Need, DJ ATG and Level 4 PR present BassicK Elements Unofficial Showcase 2013 | Music You Need | DJ ATG | Level 4 PR | DUBSTEP.NET
column12: Sound Remedy,Sazon Booya,Pound Pound Pound,Team Bayside High,Joe Mousepad,ill-esha,Knight Riderz,WORTHY,Amine Edge & DANCE,gLAdiator,Kill Paris
column13: ► 21+ from 2PM-2AM|► Ins & outs -- feel free to come and go|► FREE wristband for SXSW badge holders until 10PM!---------------------------------------------------------|Check out and make a donation to our Kickstarter Fund! If the project is fully funded we will refund all presale tickets and the show will be FREE! ➔ http://kck.st/XlURgI|---------------------------------------------------------|LINE-UP:|Headlining: Kill Paris from Los Angeles, CANEXUS from Orlando, FL### (PoundPoundPound) from West Lafayette, INTeam Bayside High from Chicago, ILValentino Khan from Los Angeles, CASound Remedy from Los Angeles, CAWorthy from Los Angeles, CAAmine Edge & DANCE from Marseille,FranceKnight Riderz from Edmonton, Canadaill-esha from Denver, COLeDoom from San Antonio, TXJoe Mousepad from San Francisco, CASazon Booya from New York City, NYgLAdiator from Los Angeles, CAVIP entry begins at 1 P.M. with: SPECIAL GUEST: NEXUS ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------PARTNERS:|Level 4 PR|www.level4pr.com|www.facebook.com/level4pr|DJ ATG|www.dj-atg.com|https://www.facebook.com/pages/DJ-ATG/376270923764?fref=ts|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------PRESENTING SPONSOR:|DUBSTEP.NETwww.dubstep.netwww.facebook.com/dubstep----------------------------------------------------------------------------------FOR OUR FULL LIST OF SPONSORS PLEASE VISIT MUSICYOUNEED.NET/BASSICKELEMENTS|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------NEXUS|Connect with Nexus|Facebook | SoundCloud|Pound Pound Pound(###)| This up and coming producer/dj duo, hailing from west Lafayette Indiana, are taking over the Midwest. In their first year of storming the EDM scene ### (pronounced Pound Pound Pound) has opened for Vibesquad, Krewella, Midnight Conspiracy, Cenob1te, Ghost House, and other awesome acts. ### has been spinning for a couple years but in 2012 they started focusing on original production. You can expect multiple individual releases and at least two e.p.'s this year. Not only are these guys putting out crazy originals and remixes like the one they did of Clique with FootwoRk, but their live show is one full of energy and bass all the way through. These guys are doing some big things this year so keep them on your radar! Are you down to pound?Connect with ###|Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud|Team Bayside High|Team Bayside High are a duo from hailing from Chicago currently putting out freaky bass music on Teenage Riot Records. Their combination of heavy sub bass, complex rhythms and melodies have been taking over dance floors by storm leaving audiences scrambling for more. Rising from a metal background, these multi-instrumentalists are bringing a fresh perspective to the world of dance music breaking tempo and genre barriers, fusing together an all encompassing audio assault. Team Bayside High is rapidly on the rise after completing several national tours, and standout festival appearances such as Lollapalooza and North Coast Music Festival. With multiple tracks breaching the top 5 in Hypem charts and receiving tons of support from some of the bigger artists in the bass game, stay tuned for Team Bayside Highs newest record being in Spring 2013.Connect with Team Bayside High|Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud|FEATURING (4 p.m. - 2 a.m.):|Kill Paris|Corey Baker aka Kill Paris has been scorching the internet blogesphere this summer. Receiving support from A-Trak, Dillon Francis, Flux Pavilion, and Skrillex. Kill Paris’s focus has been on giving his music away for free and make it easier for people to share with others. He just had his own “name your own price” album release on killparis.bandcamp.comcall “The Beginning (2012)” His also soundcloud features 23 songs that anyone can download for free. Being an Ableton Certified Trainer, his software of choice is Ableton Live. Live shows consist of 90 percent originals and remixes. Corey is currently sharing the stage all over the US with the likes of Pretty Lights, Zion I, Mimosa, AraabMuzik, Whiskey Pete, Figure, Mac Miller, Infected Mushroom, & Nicky Romero to name a few.|Connect with Kill Paris|Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | Soundcloud|Dov|Dov is the person behind Muti Music, a selector at heart, compulsively picking tunes for record labels and for your dancing / listening pleasure. He produces various bassline centric music, downtempo, midtempo and uptempo Dubstep, Drumstep, Glitch Hop, Breaks and whatever catches his fancy in the future, also receiving accolades for collaborations with ill.Gates, An-ten-nae and Funk Monsta. His sound when performing represents that of a whole movement of young producers coming out on his Muti Music imprint and adds directions that you know are going to emerge more in the future. Known for his energetic sets that delve as hard into a tranquil interlude as they do into bassline drops and glitched out frenzies. The sounds to be expected from Dov are always elevated and emotional, whether downtempo or peak time uptempo in super-clubs, his diversity and experience have prepared him for the job.Connect with Dov|Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | Soundcloud |Sound Remedy|Sound Remedy is an American electronic music producer based out of Los Angeles, California. Hailing from Chicago, SR has been crafting his sound since the young age of 16, but only started to produce music fulltime 2 years ago. Despite obtaining a degree in finance from one of the nation’s elite business schools, SR opted to take a risk and pursue his true passion; music. Being that both of his parents are graduates of Juilliard School of Music and full time Chicago Symphony Orchestra players, this decision may have been in the cards all along.|Connect with Sound Remedy|Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud|Worthy|When it comes down to all the press and hype, his name says it all. He is Worthy. With an in-depth knowledge of production, mixing, and performance, Worthy has the insight to play for his audience, cultivating intense positive energy on the dance floor that can only be portrayed as superhuman. His sound can be described as organic breakbeats with a mix of future house, 80s, booty bass, and techno. As Carl Cox said, "The Worthy sound has always been powerful, rocking, funky, bass-driven music at its best, and for me this is the new wave in house music." Worthy has received the recognition of major producers who have played his tracks including Sven Vath, Diplo, and Richie Hawtin, among many.|Connect with Worthy|Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud|Amine Edge & DANCE|Born in 1983 in South of France, Amine Edge was House, DANCE was Hip Hop. Together they mash their experience, mood and style to create their own style “G-House”, Amine Edge & DANCE are knows in France as one of the symbolic figures of the brand new "G House" movement. Basically called "Gangsta House", the name of this movement comes from the special atmosphere this music just kicks away: here comes another vision of the House music, a stunning combination between Funk’s deep basses and inspired by the latest 80s Hip House movement. So far, 2012 was a great year. Released on Exploited, Noir, Rekids, Nurvous, FFRR (Pete Tong) or 2diy4 thanks to the legendary Going To Heaven With The Goodie-Goodies. Amine Edge & DANCE are one of major artists in deep-house industry. Recently, Mark Knight himself invited Amine Edge & DANCE as Guest on his radioshow. At work for his own imprint « CUFF » or in homestudio for the fourthcoming album released on Get Physical and releases stuff in OFF Recordings & Hot Creation. 2013 will be very busy for the Bad Boys of Marseille.|Connect with Amine Edge & Dance|Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud|Knight Riderz|Canadian-based producer Nick Samalack, performing as Knight Riderz which was originally formed as a duo, hails from Edmonton, AB but spends most of his time traveling the United States, rocking crowds. Once a mainstay as a Drum n’ Bass MC in the early 2000s, Samalack continued to expand his interest in bass music and found Knight Riderz. Strongly influenced by jungle and hip-hop, Samalack dove head first into the art of product ion wit h no limit at ion on genre or style....and Knight Riderz was born.With the musical creation of Knight Riderz, Samalack, began pushing boundaries with techniques, which is what distinguishes this project and his unique live performances from others. As Knight Riderz, Samalack delivers high energy sets composed of entirely original compositions that are accompanied by cutting edge dance rhythms and dance floor-targeted bass lines.Connect with Knight Riderz|Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloudLeDoom|Doombahton -- In a matter of one short year, Texas producer LeDoom has managed to push the boundaries of dance music with his signature approach to producing tracks in the moombahton genre. This versatile and prolific young artist has already gained support from the likes of DJs and producers such as Knife Party,Dillon Francis, DJ Craze, Tittsworth, Nadastrom and Munchi, Kissy Sell Out, Bro Safari to name a few, all proponents of their own unique bass-driven styles. Their stamps of approval reveal LeDoom's power as a genre-bending tastemaker. With his first EP "Doombah", released on the El Cuco Recordings imprint, LeDoom managed to chart at #5 on the Beatport Indie Dance charts and earn the respect of gigging DJs, fellow producers and the electronic music community at large. Fast forward a few short months and LeDoom has consistently released quality new music with Mad Decent, T & A Records, Party Like Us and Play Me Records, Slow Roast Records, continually charting in the Beatport Top 100 across various genres. A distinct production talent in the studio and a crowd favorite in his live sets, LeDoom's sound and selection have organically established him as a defining artist of the moombahton family, from behind the decks of DJs to the party on the dancefloor.|Connect with LeDoom|Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloudill-eshaFor over a decade, ill-esha has been an integral part of the North American electronic scene. Beginning as a vocalist, she soon added MCing and DJing to her repertoire, creating a dynamic and unique live show which has headlined alongside artists such as Andy C, Klute, Dieselboy, Vibesquad, LTJ Bukem, Tipper, T- Power & De La Soul. She has performed across North America, Europe and Asia; in clubs, at festivals, and even on TV shows on MTV Canada and the CBC. In 2001 her first 12” single was released on New York label Breakbeat Science; since then ill-esha has worked steadily as a producer and vocalist on labels like Dub Police, Haunted Audio, Simplify & Muti Music; hitting #1 singles download on Juno and commanding six spots of the top ten in the inaugural Beatport Glitch Hop charts. One of the founding members of the premier online community GlitchHopForum.com, her remixes are hugely popular, popping up in DJ sets across the globe. Her show is a fiery combination of original beats, glitch edits and live vocals, not to be missed!|Connect with ill-esha|Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud|Sazon Booya|Moombaton production & DJ two-piece Sazon Booya (click here) made up of NYC natives Mr.Vega & DJ SAV, have been making substantial waves across the blogosphere with their original moombahton productions since the beginning of 2011, and they’ve received countless nods of respect from top tier tastemakers from around the globe ever since.Sazon Booya debuted their first track “IIuvia” via moombahton creator Dave Nada’s soundcloud and website, to much success; instantly gaining play support from Munchi, Heartbreak, DJ Sabo, Obeyah, Skrillex, Boyfriend, Fellow and of course Dave Nada himself.|Connect with Sazon Booya|Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloudgLAdiator|gLAdiator is a DJ/Production duo from Los Angeles comprised of Danl Goodman and Ian Johnson. The two have established themselves as heavy hitters in the Trap/Bass-music game and show no signs of slowing down. They show their flex and diverse backgrounds by melding their collected musical taste and experience into a sound unique to gLAdiator. VIP entry begins at 1 P.M. with: SPECIAL GUEST: NEXUS

Level 4 PR

www.dubstep.net

FOR OUR FULL LIST OF SPONSORS PLEASE VISIT MUSICYOUNEED.NET/BASSICKELEMENTS

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NEXUS

Connect with Nexus
Facebook | SoundCloud

Pound Pound Pound(###)

This up and coming producer/dj duo, hailing from west Lafayette Indiana, are taking over the Midwest. In their first year of storming the EDM scene ### (pronounced Pound Pound Pound) has opened for Vibesquad, Krewella, Midnight Conspiracy, Cenob1te, Ghost House, and other awesome acts. ### has been spinning for a couple years but in 2012 they started focusing on original production. You can expect multiple individual releases and at least two e.p.'s this year. Not only are these guys putting out crazy originals and remixes like the one they did of Clique with FootwoRk, but their live show is one full of energy and bass all the way through. These guys are doing some big things this year so keep them on your radar! Are you down to pound?

Connect with ###
Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

Team Bayside High

Team Bayside High are a duo from hailing from Chicago currently putting out freaky bass music on Teenage Riot Records. Their combination of heavy sub bass, complex rhythms and melodies have been taking over dance floors by storm leaving audiences scrambling for more. Rising from a metal background, these multi-instrumentalists are bringing a fresh perspective to the world of dance music breaking tempo and genre barriers, fusing together an all encompassing audio assault. Team Bayside High is rapidly on the rise after completing several national tours, and standout festival appearances such as Lollapalooza and North Coast Music Festival. With multiple tracks breaching the top 5 in Hypem charts and receiving tons of support from some of the bigger artists in the bass game, stay tuned for Team Bayside Highs newest record being in Spring 2013.

Connect with Team Bayside High
Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

FEATURING (4 p.m. - 2 a.m.):

Kill Paris

Corey Baker aka Kill Paris has been scorching the internet blogesphere this summer. Receiving support from A-Trak, Dillon Francis, Flux Pavilion, and Skrillex. Kill Paris’s focus has been on giving his music away for free and make it easier for people to share with others. He just had his own “name your own price” album release on killparis.bandcamp.comcall “The Beginning (2012)” His also soundcloud features 23 songs that anyone can download for free. Being an Ableton Certified Trainer, his software of choice is Ableton Live. Live shows consist of 90 percent originals and remixes. Corey is currently sharing the stage all over the US with the likes of Pretty Lights, Zion I, Mimosa, AraabMuzik, Whiskey Pete, Figure, Mac Miller, Infected Mushroom, & Nicky Romero to name a few.

Connect with Kill Paris
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | Soundcloud

Dov

Dov is the person behind Muti Music, a selector at heart, compulsively picking tunes for record labels and for your dancing / listening pleasure. He produces various bassline centric music, downtempo, midtempo and uptempo Dubstep, Drumstep, Glitch Hop, Breaks and whatever catches his fancy in the future, also receiving accolades for collaborations with ill.Gates, An-ten-nae and Funk Monsta. His sound when performing represents that of a whole movement of young producers coming out on his Muti Music imprint and adds directions that you know are going to emerge more in the future. Known for his energetic sets that delve as hard into a tranquil interlude as they do into bassline drops and glitched out frenzies. The sounds to be expected from Dov are always elevated and emotional, whether downtempo or peak time uptempo in super-clubs, his diversity and experience have prepared him for the job.

Connect with Dov
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | Soundcloud

Sound Remedy

Sound Remedy is an American electronic music producer based out of Los Angeles, California. Hailing from Chicago, SR has been crafting his sound since the young age of 16, but only started to produce music fulltime 2 years ago. Despite obtaining a degree in finance from one of the nation’s elite business schools, SR opted to take a risk and pursue his true passion; music. Being that both of his parents are graduates of Juilliard School of Music and full time Chicago Symphony Orchestra players, this decision may have been in the cards all along.

Connect with Sound Remedy
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

Worthy

When it comes down to all the press and hype, his name says it all. He is Worthy. With an in-depth knowledge of production, mixing, and performance, Worthy has the insight to play for his audience, cultivating intense positive energy on the dance floor that can only be portrayed as superhuman. His sound can be described as organic breakbeats with a mix of future house, 80s, booty bass, and techno. As Carl Cox said, "The Worthy sound has always been powerful, rocking, funky, bass-driven music at its best, and for me this is the new wave in house music." Worthy has received the recognition of major producers who have played his tracks including Sven Vath, Diplo, and Richie Hawtin, among many.

Connect with Worthy
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

Amine Edge & DANCE

Born in 1983 in South of France, Amine Edge was House, DANCE was Hip Hop. Together they mash their experience, mood and style to create their own style “G-House”, Amine Edge & DANCE are knows in France as one of the symbolic figures of the brand new "G House" movement. Basically called "Gangsta House", the name of this movement comes from the special atmosphere this music just kicks away: here comes another vision of the House music, a stunning combination between Funk’s deep basses and inspired by the latest 80s Hip House movement. So far, 2012 was a great year. Released on Exploited, Noir, Rekids, Nurvous, FFRR (Pete Tong) or 2diy4 thanks to the legendary Going To Heaven With The Goodie-Goodies. Amine Edge & DANCE are one of major artists in deep-house industry. Recently, Mark Knight himself invited Amine Edge & DANCE as Guest on his radioshow. At work for his own imprint « CUFF » or in homestudio for the fourthcoming album released on Get Physical and releases stuff in OFF Recordings & Hot Creation. 2013 will be very busy for the Bad Boys of Marseille.

Connect with Amine Edge & Dance
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

Knight Riderz

Canadian-based producer Nick Samalack, performing as Knight Riderz which was originally formed as a duo, hails from Edmonton, AB but spends most of his time traveling the United States, rocking crowds. Once a mainstay as a Drum n’ Bass MC in the early 2000s, Samalack continued to expand his interest in bass music and found Knight Riderz. Strongly influenced by jungle and hip-hop, Samalack dove head first into the art of product ion wit h no limit at ion on genre or style....and Knight Riderz was born.With the musical creation of Knight Riderz, Samalack, began pushing boundaries with techniques, which is what distinguishes this project and his unique live performances from others. As Knight Riderz, Samalack delivers high energy sets composed of entirely original compositions that are accompanied by cutting edge dance rhythms and dance floor-targeted bass lines.

Connect with Knight Riderz
Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

LeDoom

Doombahton -- In a matter of one short year, Texas producer LeDoom has managed to push the boundaries of dance music with his signature approach to producing tracks in the moombahton genre. This versatile and prolific young artist has already gained support from the likes of DJs and producers such as Knife Party,Dillon Francis, DJ Craze, Tittsworth, Nadastrom and Munchi, Kissy Sell Out, Bro Safari to name a few, all proponents of their own unique bass-driven styles. Their stamps of approval reveal LeDoom's power as a genre-bending tastemaker. With his first EP "Doombah", released on the El Cuco Recordings imprint, LeDoom managed to chart at #5 on the Beatport Indie Dance charts and earn the respect of gigging DJs, fellow producers and the electronic music community at large. Fast forward a few short months and LeDoom has consistently released quality new music with Mad Decent, T & A Records, Party Like Us and Play Me Records, Slow Roast Records, continually charting in the Beatport Top 100 across various genres. A distinct production talent in the studio and a crowd favorite in his live sets, LeDoom's sound and selection have organically established him as a defining artist of the moombahton family, from behind the decks of DJs to the party on the dancefloor.

Connect with LeDoom
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

ill-esha

For over a decade, ill-esha has been an integral part of the North American electronic scene. Beginning as a vocalist, she soon added MCing and DJing to her repertoire, creating a dynamic and unique live show which has headlined alongside artists such as Andy C, Klute, Dieselboy, Vibesquad, LTJ Bukem, Tipper, T- Power & De La Soul. She has performed across North America, Europe and Asia; in clubs, at festivals, and even on TV shows on MTV Canada and the CBC. In 2001 her first 12” single was released on New York label Breakbeat Science; since then ill-esha has worked steadily as a producer and vocalist on labels like Dub Police, Haunted Audio, Simplify & Muti Music; hitting #1 singles download on Juno and commanding six spots of the top ten in the inaugural Beatport Glitch Hop charts. One of the founding members of the premier online community GlitchHopForum.com, her remixes are hugely popular, popping up in DJ sets across the globe. Her show is a fiery combination of original beats, glitch edits and live vocals, not to be missed!

Connect with ill-esha
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

Sazon Booya

Moombaton production & DJ two-piece Sazon Booya (click here) made up of NYC natives Mr.Vega & DJ SAV, have been making substantial waves across the blogosphere with their original moombahton productions since the beginning of 2011, and they’ve received countless nods of respect from top tier tastemakers from around the globe ever since.Sazon Booya debuted their first track “IIuvia” via moombahton creator Dave Nada’s soundcloud and website, to much success; instantly gaining play support from Munchi, Heartbreak, DJ Sabo, Obeyah, Skrillex, Boyfriend, Fellow and of course Dave Nada himself.

Connect with Sazon Booya
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

gLAdiator
gLAdiator is a DJ/Production duo from Los Angeles comprised of Danl Goodman and Ian Johnson. The two have established themselves as heavy hitters in the Trap/Bass-music game and show no signs of slowing down. They show their flex and diverse backgrounds by melding their collected musical taste and experience into a sound unique to gLAdiator. Their love of the Lakers and all things Mila Kunis fuels their productive fire with the aim of making a name for themselves in the wonderful melting pot they call home, Los Angeles.

Connect with gLAdiator
Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

column13: YELAWOLF: TRUNK MUZIK RETURNS RELEASE PARTY @ CLUB DE VILLE|Envision a humid world of slow-rolling Monte Carlos and slaughter houses; meth labs and rusting Mossberg’s, inked up arms and haircuts that look like they’ve been chopped by hatchets. Trunk Muzik. Southern Pine trees, smoking pine, and pine boxes. Call him Catfish Billy or Yelawolf, just don’t go make him go pop the trunk on you.|Enter Yelawolf’s Alabama—a backwoods badlands of sinners and salvation. He claims Gadsden, but he’s from everywhere. Born Michael Wayne Atha to an absentee father and a bartender mother, he attended over 15 schools while soaking up slang and spiritualism in Baton Rouge, Antioch, Tennessee, and Atlanta. While trying to stay afloat in a turbulent home life addled by drug and alcohol abuse, he discovered rap music in Tennessee and it soon became an obsession, along with the classic rock (Lynard Skynard, Pink Floyd, The Allman Brothers) that he was raised on. |via Monster Bands
column14:
YELAWOLF: TRUNK MUZIK RETURNS RELEASE PARTY @ CLUB DE VILLE

Envision a humid world of slow-rolling Monte Carlos and slaughter houses; meth labs and rusting Mossberg’s, inked up arms and haircuts that look like they’ve been chopped by hatchets. Trunk Muzik. Southern Pine trees, smoking pine, and pine boxes. Call him Catfish Billy or Yelawolf, just don’t go make him go pop the trunk on you.

Enter Yelawolf’s Alabama—a backwoods badlands of sinners and salvation. He claims Gadsden, but he’s from everywhere. Born Michael Wayne Atha to an absentee father and a bartender mother, he attended over 15 schools while soaking up slang and spiritualism in Baton Rouge, Antioch, Tennessee, and Atlanta. While trying to stay afloat in a turbulent home life addled by drug and alcohol abuse, he discovered rap music in Tennessee and it soon became an obsession, along with the classic rock (Lynard Skynard, Pink Floyd, The Allman Brothers) that he was raised on.

via Monster Bands

column14:
Long time SXSW Super Sponsor IFC is back and they are bringing their "Always On - Slightly Off" sense of humor with them as presenters of the newest official Comedy Stage of SXSW 2013. The network that has brought you countless side-splitting shows like Portlandia, The Whitest Kids U'Know and Comedy Bang! Bang! will be delivering four days of comedy from the IFC Crossroads House, located at Vice bar on 6th Street.


Last year some of the biggest names in comedy made their way through the Crossroads House including Reggie Watts, Jay Chandrasekhar, Mike Birbiglia and many more. It's a safe bet that IFC will have equally impressive talent on stage this year doing what they do best. It looks like the future of the Trapped in the Closet series might not be the number one thing you're looking forward to this year from our friends over at IFC anymore.


Keep an eye on ifc.com/sxsw for announcements on what you can expect March 9 through March 12 at the IFC Crossroads House.


Comedy lineups coming soon!

column14:
#FEED powered by Twitter - 2013 SXSW Interactive


Featuring:


Interactive Social Media Art

Turning "the cloud" into real-time social media art installations, created by leading interactive artists, that tell the SXSW story day and night.


Mind + Body + Tech Sanctuary

Morning rooftop sessions with yoga, meditation, boot camp, and spinning. Snacks, juice, coffee, and Lunch Break DJ dance parties.


Daylong Media Summits

Join leading thinkers, tech startups, brands, and storytellers each day with afternoon programs meant to inspire and ignite creativity.


@Night Dance Parties

One Funktion 1 sound system and world-class electronic musical talent will melt the walls while keeping the party going each night through 2am.


#FEED powered by Twitter is a five day and @NIGHT event that tells the story of SXSWi as an interactive + social media + art + technology + wellness experience.


Now in its second year on the beautiful AMOA-Arthouse at the Jones Center, #FEED resonates with an audience as savvy as it is engaged, turning the online social media experience into interactive art while hosting electronic music dance parties @NIGHT that set the bar in both buzz and talent curation.


The 2013 series will also feature daily Storytelling Summits hosted by leading brands, as well as a Mind+Body+Tech Sanctuary and Sunset Mixers on the beautiful AMOA- Arthouse rooftop overlooking downtown Austin.


Produced by Justin Bolognino's Brooklyn-based Learned Evolution, a brand ID, website, experience design and mobile platform agency, #FEED promises to be the hit of the 25th annual SXSW.

"The event changed the way most people see art by transforming it into an interactive experience and joining it with real-time trending topics.” -FORBES


"Twitter's #FEED space with fantastic digital representations of the company's tra c. The number of parties was as staggering as the length of lines to get in some of them." -BILLBOARD


"A #romance is born" -TIME

column14:
MashBash at SXSWi 2013 Details
Date: Sunday, March 10, 2013
Time: 9 p.m. to 2 a.m.
Location: Speakeasy, 412 Congress Ave, Austin, Texas


RSVP Policy
The event is open to all 21+ SXSWi badge holders. Please RSVP on Eventbrite.


We're happy to announce the return of MashBash at SXSWi 2013! Amid the plethora of panels, presentations and parties, Mashable will be hosting one of the biggest and most memorable events in Austin.


Join Mashable and the SXSWi community on Sunday, March 10 from 9 p.m. to 2 a.m. for an evening of music, dancing and digital inspiration, along with an open bar. And as always, there will be a few surprises along the way.


Joining us as the talent behind the turntables will be DJ Mick Boogie, whose arsenal of tunes range from 80s, rock and soul, to disco, house and electro. Make sure to come with your dancing shoes on.


Our MashBash sponsors Yappem and 3M will make the evening truly unique with their special digital activations, which will be revealed at the party.

In addition to the MashBash on Sunday night, we have some exciting plans that we'll be announcing soon, so stay tuned!


Socialize
Follow #MashSXSW on Twitter, Facebook, Google+, Foursquare, and Instagram.



via Mashable.com

column14:
For the 4th consecutive year, we'll be kicking off the gdgt live Tour down in Austin and we'd love to have you there.



Come out, have a drink and check out some of today's hottest new gear and services. We'll have the list of sponsors posted on the gdgt live site very soon.



As always, gdgt live is FREE to attend and SXSW badges are not required.


We'll have free gdgt t-shirts for the first several hundred attendees so be sure to get there early if you want one.

Everyone who shows up will have plenty of chances to win some awesome stuff from our great sponsors.

Unfortunately, due to circumstances beyond our control, this event is 21+ only. We're not happy about it, but all our other 2013 gdgt live events will open to everyone...



gdgt live is the only tech event series specifically designed to give actual consumers a chance to connect face-to-face with todays top tech companies and hottest startups.


Make sure to tell your friends and share info on the event on your social networks. The official Twitter hashtag is @gdgtaustin.


Look forward to seeing you there!


- via Eventbrite

column13: SX2013 Line-up to Come...|RSVP for FREE NOW!|First 30 bands added to line-up: BattlemeCaged AnimalsCarouselChina RatsCITIZENS!Darwin DeezDuologueFrench Horn RebellionFuneral SuitsGemini ClubGhost BeachGlass TowersHalf Moon RunHey ChampHigh HighsHudson TaylorHumansJonathan BouletLetting Up Despite Great FaultsLovelifeOn an OnThe RocketboysRoyal BathsRoyal CanoeSlow MagicSuburban LivingTremor LowTerraplane SunWild ClubWildcat! Wildcat!|This year, we at Beautiful Buzzz are teaming up with Beagle Freedom Project to present our 3rd SXSW unofficial showcase, FREE NOW! FREE NOW! will take place March 13 -16, four days and nights during the SXSW Music Conference, from 12pm to 2am at The Brew Exchange in downtown Austin, Texas. Over 100 bands will be selected to present and create awareness for the Beagle Freedom Project. This gives attendees, performers and sponsors the opportunity to give back to the global community.|BEAUTIFUL BUZZZ (WWW.BEAUTIFULBUZZZ.COM)|Beautiful Buzzz is a new music blog based out of San Francisco, CA. Our goal is to expose up-and-coming artists who we believe are on the cutting edge of indie rock, electronic and dance music. We believe the world needs to know about the little guys – and we love to support independent musicians from around the globe! The name comes from a Rolling Stones song called “Loving Cup” which happens to be Editor/Founder Erin Maher’s favorite song from the British rockers. It’s not a reference to anything else but that – but we like to think we have our finger on the pulse of what is buzzing within the indie music scene. The site caters to those interested in music news and goings on within the Los Angeles, San Francisco, United Kingdom, and Australian music scene, although does not exclude any other regions.The site includes: a new music section, gig guide, record and show reviews, links to videos and other interesting music related items around the web, and a mix tape section complied monthly and showcasing some of the best music available at the time of its creation.

This year, we at Beautiful Buzzz are teaming up with Beagle Freedom Project to present our 3rd SXSW unofficial showcase, FREE NOW! FREE NOW! will take place March 13 -16, four days and nights during the SXSW Music Conference, from 12pm to 2am at The Brew Exchange in downtown Austin, Texas. Over 100 bands will be selected to present and create awareness for the Beagle Freedom Project. This gives attendees, performers and sponsors the opportunity to give back to the global community.



BEAUTIFUL BUZZZ (WWW.BEAUTIFULBUZZZ.COM)

Beautiful Buzzz is a new music blog based out of San Francisco, CA. Our goal is to expose up-and-coming artists who we believe are on the cutting edge of indie rock, electronic and dance music. We believe the world needs to know about the little guys – and we love to support independent musicians from around the globe!

The name comes from a Rolling Stones song called “Loving Cup” which happens to be Editor/Founder Erin Maher’s favorite song from the British rockers. It’s not a reference to anything else but that – but we like to think we have our finger on the pulse of what is buzzing within the indie music scene. The site caters to those interested in music news and goings on within the Los Angeles, San Francisco, United Kingdom, and Australian music scene, although does not exclude any other regions.

The site includes: a new music section, gig guide, record and show reviews, links to videos and other interesting music related items around the web, and a mix tape section complied monthly and showcasing some of the best music available at the time of its creation.

column14:
RSVP

*FREE*

THE LINE-UP (not in order of appearance):

Andrew Duncan Brown and The Dirty Rascals:
Andrew’s moody singing is entrancing, rooted in folk and delta-blues coupled with rock music elements. Simple, yet full of emotion; there is something deeper that lies at the heart of every song. The melody intoxicates the listeners by allowing them to form their own relationship and attachment with the songs.
http://www.andrewduncanbrown.com/

Avery:
Avery formed in March of 2011 by Allison Galbreath and Mariah DeRaet. After playing together for a couple months Brad Mitchell joined the mix and changed the game by further producing their simplistic stylings with slide guitars and ambient lead parts. In July of 2012 some heavier percussion was needed and Eric Estrada was happy to oblige.
www.reverbnation.com/averyaz

Bad Lucy:
The trio of J. Miller, Alex Kyhn and Alex Lee are an amalgamation of differing influences that meld into their unique style known for its nuance, use of space and surprising harmonies. J. Miller pulls heavily from his folk sensibilities when writing and performing, while bassist Alex Kyhn brings to the fold a mix of jazz and soul. Drummer Alex Lee’s marching and rock roots add the final layer.

Officially formed in March 2011, the band showcased their sounds on a self-titled release in May 2012. The debut, which was recorded live to tape, came on the heels of a year of highs for the band including the broadcast of their single “Forward” on the Macy’s Thanksgiving Day Parade. The song was also a “homegrown hit” on the local, Phoenix airwaves.

Known for “sounding just like the recording” during their live performances, the band often silences a room within minutes. A reviewer/blogger, that was first introduced to the band via a live stream, sums it up best: "The band is called Bad Lucy, and their gorgeous, melodic songs and energetic live show blasted right through the off-kilter webcam and livestream hiccups—and into my heart. Shut up, I’m serious."
www.badlucyband.com

Captain Squeegee:
"The Gods of Music are not dead! They are coming out of retirement for this young group brimming with talent, enthusiasm, and freshness" (French-Webzine "Progressia"). In a world strangled by mediocrity and distraction, Captain Squeegee leads a legacy to push the boundaries of music and bend the rules of the industry itself. Since their mysterious formation in 2003, they have allowed fate to arrange their current line-up (no original members), which has since performed hundreds of shows and festivals, released two albums, and manifested multiple music videos. Even before birthing their internationally acclaimed full length, Nothing vs Everything (2008), the band has made numerous journeys across the southwest with an intent to infect the people with their unique sound and offer something seriously different to the artistic community. Their progressive blend of multi-instrumentation and conceptualized orchestrations have been described as "Fantasia music, with lead singer Danny Torgersen making like Mickey in a swirling maelstrom of flying horns, dancing guitars, broken melodies, and mad-prophet vocalizing" (Phoenix New Times), and was even awarded "Best album of 2008" and "Best hope of 2009" by French Webzine-"Progressia". Recently, they have paired up with the "Lucidity Web-Saga" as actors and musicians, even writing it's theme song, "Your Own Invention", which they recorded in a pyramid. Forever in stark contrast to the robotic, zombie infested waters of the mass media and mainstream, Squeegee will continue to offer a new age perspective, driving their fans and future fans to open the mind's eye (and ear)... and "See More Clearly".
www.captainsqueegee.com

Danger Paul:
Danger Paul consists of Paul Balazs (guitar/vocals), Calin Gross (guitar/lap steel slide), Keith Fama (bass), and Ari Leopold (drums). With a wide variety of influence the only simple working description is JAZZ GRUNGE.
http://dangerpaul.bandcamp.com/

Japhy’s Descent:
Japhy's Descent is about planting seeds to watch our community grow. Music has brought us & those around us so much joy, that we wish to share that love with the world around us. Brian, Martin, James & Travis wish to invite you to take the plunge into the wonderful world around you. Listen to music, laugh, play, love, share, & experience the awe around you by simply being apart of it. Remember... "You can't fall off a mountain".
www.reverbnation.com/japhysdescent

Field Tripp:
Field Tripp is an American alternative rock band based in Phoenix, AZ. The band was formed in 2007 as a three-piece by songwriters Dan Allmond, Jonathon Smith, and Matthew Newcomb. The trio released one self-titled 5 song EP in late 2007. Field Tripp's roster has changed frequently, with only singer/guitarist Dan Allmond remaining from the original lineup. Since mid 2011 the other members include multi-instrumentalists Eliz Christy and Brian Mabry with Amir Azzabi on drums. The band has developed a reputation for their raw yet poppy sound, use of unconventional instruments, and strong songwriting. Field Tripp released their first full length album entitled Super-Ego Friendly in 2011 and is currently recording their second album due for release in Summer 2013.
www.reverbnation.com/fieldtripp

Frequent Kings:
Frequent Kings originally started with Glenn Nishida and WuT then migrated to WuT and Kamakane who Met in Hawaii through a musical mutual friend. “ Now...... Frequent Kings Consist of Band that is sticking like Hot glue melted. WuT (Tim), Guitarist ,Vocalist, and occasional harmonica player... the Pocket playing Drummer Josh, and The laid Back Bassist and Keyboardist Ryan. Occcasionally Kamakane lead Guitarist comes in from Hawaii to grace us with his Masterful skills. This combination of players has evolved in a next generation Dirty Blues, new to old school Low Flow, Vibed Out organically based Fresh Band! Currently were Playing steady Gigs, mixed with originals and Covers.
COME ON IN!
www.frequentkings.com

Sundressed:
Sundressed is a 4-piece indie rock band from Tempe Arizona comprised of songwriter Trevor Hedges, GUitarist Tyler Kees, Bassist Evan Kees and Garrett Tretta. Their sound is a mix of a variety of influences from bright eyes to the Doors. They formed in November of 2011. Since then they have released a very promising ep and are currently wrapping up their first full length record. Sundressed has been described as taking a Neil young song and playing it with the punk rock fury of the pixies. Be sure to check out their showcase at sxsw!
http://sundressed.bandcamp.com

The Hourglass Cats:
Forming together in the dusty southwest, The Hourglass Cats are a high energy five piece outfit with members from NY, Germany, CA, and AZ. THC brings a wide range of influences to the table to create a truly unique genre-defying soundscape. Their music has heavy roots in Latin Reggae/Ska, RockNRoll, Funk, and Hip hop.
www.iheartthc.com

This year, we at Beautiful Buzzz are teaming up with Beagle Freedom Project to present our 3rd SXSW unofficial showcase, FREE NOW! FREE NOW! will take place March 13 -16, four days and nights during the SXSW Music Conference, from 12pm to 2am at The Brew Exchange in downtown Austin, Texas. Over 100 bands will be selected to present and create awareness for the Beagle Freedom Project. This gives attendees, performers and sponsors the opportunity to give back to the global community.









BEAUTIFUL BUZZZ (WWW.BEAUTIFULBUZZZ.COM)
Beautiful Buzzz is a new music blog based out of San Francisco, CA. Our goal is to expose up-and-coming artists who we believe are on the cutting edge of indie rock, electronic and dance music. We believe the world needs to know about the little guys – and we love to support independent musicians from around the globe!
The name comes from a Rolling Stones song called “Loving Cup” which happens to be Editor/Founder Erin Maher’s favorite song from the British rockers. It’s not a reference to anything else but that – but we like to think we have our finger on the pulse of what is buzzing within the indie music scene. The site caters to those interested in music news and goings on within the Los Angeles, San Francisco, United Kingdom, and Australian music scene, although does not exclude any other regions.
The site includes: a new music section, gig guide, record and show reviews, links to videos and other interesting music related items around the web, and a mix tape section complied monthly and showcasing some of the best music available at the time of its creation.

column14:
Join Tech Cocktail as we celebrate some of the world's hottest startups on the grand stage at SXSW.


We're finalizing the details for SXSW 2013, but you can rest assured it's going to be an action packed day, concluding with a massive Tech Cocktail Mixer (which is code for party).


This marks Tech Cocktail's fourth annual SXSW bash. Chances are, if you've been to SXSW in years' past, you're familiar with how we roll. In case you missed the previous festivities, check these links from SXSW 2012, SXSW 2011 and SXSW 2010.

Showcasing Startups
Past showcased startups at our events have gotten great feedback, been funded on the spot, met new employees, investors, and some have even be acquired. Some of our SXSW showcased startup alumni include FitOrbit, Foodspotting, Khush, Mobile Roadie, Personal, Storify, Udemy, Tango, SaneBox, Sawbuck, Sifteo, Sonar, Sphero, Stitch Labs, Votizen, and many more.


Showcase Your Startup
Want to showcase your startup in front of hundreds of fellow technology enthusiasts, investors, and high profile media? You can - simply fill out the application here.


Interested in Sponsoring?
Sponsorship opportunities are available for all the various activities. If you are interested contact us here and we’ll circle back with the SXSW information.

Event details:

When: Saturday, March 9th, 2011 at 6:00 p.m. till the cows come home

Where: The Stage on Sixth, 508 East 6th Street, Austin, TX

What: A cocktail of tech and startup enthusiasts

Price: Free with a SXSW badge (must be 21+ years old to enter)

***RSVP does not guarantee entrance. First come first serve.

THANK YOU TO OUR SPONSOR!!!

Gold Sponsor, CO


Tech Cocktail (http://tech.co) is a media company that covers the latest tech innovations across the globe. Tech Cocktail has been hosting mixer events and writing about technology start-ups and entrepreneurs across the country with the focus of helping to amplify the local technology signal since 2006. We have hosted large events in Chicago, D.C., NY, San Francisco, Boston, Boulder, San Diego, Detroit, Boise, Austin, Barcelona and more. Read more about Tech Cocktail.

column2: Boot Campaign's "Friends With Benefits" Party During SXSW
column12: Cody Canada,Sunny Sweeney,Aaron Watson,Sons of Fathers,Six Market Blvd,Midnight River Choir,The Rankin Twins
column13: Boot Campaign to Throw “Friends With Benefits” Party During SXSW 2013| Performances by Cody Canada, Sunny Sweeney, Aaron Watson, Sons of Fathers, Six Market Boulevard, Midnight River Choir, The Rankin Twins and surprise guests! Looking for a truly unique experience during SXSW? KOKE FM and Wild Turkey present the Boot Campaign’s “Friends With Benefits” party during SXSW. “Friends With Benefits” features performances by Cody Canada, Sunny Sweeney, Aaron Watson, Sons of Fathers, Six Market Blvd, Midnight River Choir, The Rankin Twins and other surprise guests! The Boot Campaign’s “Friends With Benefits” party during SXSW is March 12, 2013 at Peckerheads on Austin’s famed 6th Street. “Friends With Benefits” will directly benefit the Boot Campaign’s programs that are caring for military personnel, past and present, healing from a variety of physical and emotional combat wounds. Doors open at 7:00pm with your “Friends With Benefits” hosts Rita Ballou of Rawhide and Velvet, and KOKE FM’s Eric Raines and Drew Bennett. The party will feature live music on two stages, raffle, and more! Wild Turkey and Shiner Beers will be the featured beverages of the night, with a portion of your drink purchases being donated back to the Boot Campaign. “Friends With Benefits” is an intimate concert experience. Tickets are extremely limited, so purchase yours today on http://bit.ly/FWBSXSW For those who cannot attend, the Boot Campaign is partnering with KOKE-FM and Stage It to offer a live radio broadcast and online video stream of the concert. Details on how to watch and listen will be posted on www.KOKEFM.com and www.BootCampaign.com The “Friends with Benefits” party wouldn’t be possible with out these supporters: KOKE-FM, Wild Turkey, Peckerheads, Rawhide and Velvet, Shiner Beers, and Stage It. About The Boot Campaign The Boot Campaign is a national 501c3 patriotic movement that is dedicated to showing tangible appreciation of our active military, raising awareness of the challenges they face upon return and supporting their transition home. Through the sale of its signature military combat boots, general public donations, and corporate sponsorship, the Boot Campaign operates five distinct programs -- Jobs, Housing, Family Support, Urgent Assistance and Wellness-- that are caring for military personnel, past and present, healing from a variety of physical and emotional combat wounds, embodying the campaign motto that, “When They Come Back, We Give Back”. www.BootCampaign.com * Media Contact: Meghan McDermott Meghan@BootCampaign.com * Join the line up: Larry Murray Booking@BootCampaign.com

column14:
The “Kingdom Experience” will take place on Saturday, March 16 from 10am – 4pm at the Carver Cultural Center (as it has been since 2009) and will be comprised of concerts and panel discussions about music ministry.


It is an official SXSW event and, as in the past, it will be FREE and open to the public. Attendees will NOT need a SXSW badge or wristband to get in.


A separate showcase by Reach Records (including Lecrae, Andy Mineo, and others) will also be held earlier in the week.


The first round of artists lined up for this event include:

  • Jin
  • Da’ T.R.U.T.H.
  • The Digital Age (aka the Dave Crowder Band minus Dave Crowder)
  • Sho Baraka
  • V Rose
  • FLAME
  • Eshon Burgundy
  • DJ DMD
  • Johnathan McReynolds
  • The W.A.R.R.I.O.R.S. ATX
  • Willie Moore, Jr.
  • Propaganda


Stay tuned for more details.

Our goal is to expose up-and-coming artists who we believe are on the cutting edge of indie rock, electronic and dance music. We believe the world needs to know about the little guys – and we love to support independent musicians from around the globe! The name comes from a Rolling Stones song called “Loving Cup” which happens to be Editor/Founder Erin Maher’s favorite song from the British rockers. It’s not a reference to anything else but that – but we like to think we have our finger on the pulse of what is buzzing within the indie music scene. The site caters to those interested in music news and goings on within the Los Angeles, San Francisco, United Kingdom, and Australian music scene, although does not exclude any other regions.The site includes: a new music section, gig guide, record and show reviews, links to videos and other interesting music related items around the web, and a mix tape section complied monthly and showcasing some of the best music available at the time of its creation.
