This year, we at Beautiful Buzzz are teaming up with Beagle Freedom Project to present our 3rd SXSW unofficial showcase, FREE NOW! FREE NOW! will take place March 13 -16, four days and nights during the SXSW Music Conference, from 12pm to 2am at The Brew Exchange in downtown Austin, Texas. Over 100 bands will be selected to present and create awareness for the Beagle Freedom Project. This gives attendees, performers and sponsors the opportunity to give back to the global community.



BEAUTIFUL BUZZZ (WWW.BEAUTIFULBUZZZ.COM)

Beautiful Buzzz is a new music blog based out of San Francisco, CA. Our goal is to expose up-and-coming artists who we believe are on the cutting edge of indie rock, electronic and dance music. We believe the world needs to know about the little guys – and we love to support independent musicians from around the globe!

The name comes from a Rolling Stones song called “Loving Cup” which happens to be Editor/Founder Erin Maher’s favorite song from the British rockers. It’s not a reference to anything else but that – but we like to think we have our finger on the pulse of what is buzzing within the indie music scene. The site caters to those interested in music news and goings on within the Los Angeles, San Francisco, United Kingdom, and Australian music scene, although does not exclude any other regions.

The site includes: a new music section, gig guide, record and show reviews, links to videos and other interesting music related items around the web, and a mix tape section complied monthly and showcasing some of the best music available at the time of its creation.

column14:
A Mid West Festival + Unofficial Showcase Event during SX in Austin, TX March 12th - 17th, 2013.

This is an Unofficial SXSW Event and brought to you by BSHR Entertainment and Sponsored by Music Saves Lives


THE VENUE

The Firehouse Lounge features classically prepared cocktails, delectable accompaniments, an inviting atmosphere, and a variety of live music. Elevate your experience at Downtown's NEWEST venue.


FEATURING. . .

The giftbags will be given out at the VIP Dinner Party and the Main Event. Mini Moo Business Cards will contain download codes for guests to return home and enter for more goodies!


Plus play the Indie Band Drinking Game + Sky Scavenger Hunt all week to win Sponsored Prize Packages!

THE [SOS] SCHEDULE of SHOWS

Tuesday 3/12 Welcome to Austin: A Singer/Songwriter Party + Evening Events


Wednesday 3/13 Rockin’ Zombie Luau Day Party + Evening Events


Thursday 3/14 The Calm Before the Storm Day Party and the VIP Dinner + Cocktail Party+ evening events.

Mini spa treatments, an art gala with VIP Dinner + Cocktail party.

Friday 3/15 Blue Sky on Broadway + The Indie Dance Party: Bring on the Weekend

The start of the Vinyl Record Club in Partnership with Broadway Recording Company.


Saturday 3/16 BSHR’s “Giant” Launch Party

The main event complete with miniature EVERYTHING. Guests receive The “Grow it @ Home” Giftbag. Raffles of various prizes and giveaways.


Sunday 3/17 The Green Giant Party + Closing events

column2: M.I.A. Drum N Bass and Quadbeat Present M.I.A. Unofficial Showcase w/ Danny The Wildchild
column12: Danny The Wild Child
column13: Join us from 1pm to 5pm for MIA's opening ceremonies. Meet and greet with all the djs. Giveaways will be abundant during this time also.|DJs will be rotating from 1pm to 2am to bring you 13 hours of Drum and Bass bangers!|➩http://miadnb.com/|➩https://www.facebook.com/MIADNBDJS?fref=ts|➩https://www.facebook.com/pages/MIA-Texas-CentralSur/117609258347410|21 and up w/ proper identification.|NO COVER|M.I.A. CREW:|★•´´¯`• DANNY THE WILD CHILD|(compression san francisco / sound solution digital / rockers 175 / m.i.a. dnb chicago)|Danny the Wildchild aka Daniel Garcia was born on the South side of Chicago in 1977. The brother of a once aspiring DJ, he keenly watched and quickly learned the tricks of the trade. Danny began djing at age nine soon surpassing his brother’s abilities and eventually inherited his equipment and records. At twelve, Danny entered a Chicago area contest for young DJ’s and won. He took home that fifty-dollar prize and was called “The Wildchild” from that day forward.......|https://www.facebook.com/pages/Danny-The-Wildchild/115971325117979|http://soundcloud.com/danny-the-wildchild|★•´´¯`•ALFONZ "DELAMOTA" |(combat records / high $ociety / m.i.a. dnb chicago)|His name is synonymous with Chicago drum n bass and for being one of the founders and president of one of Americas largest drum n bass music groups, the M.I.A. (murda In america). DELAMOTA got his start djing the after-hours and small underground parties in Chicago during the early 90's rave scene as a dj, in 1998 he decided to start a production company called Sky High and put on several shows with attendance as high as 8500 people in a three room venue. With his dedication to the dnb sound he managed to travel all over the United States, Alfonz has played well over 25 cities in over 20 states both headlining and djing along side some of the worlds top electronic music producers and djs.|https://www.facebook.com/pages/Alfonz-DeLaMota/235722766465723|http://www.soundcloud.com/alfonzdelamota|★•´´¯`•RAGGA SCUM |(congo natty / cymbalism recordings / m.i.a. dnb kansas city) |Ragga Scum is widely known for his inhuman technical style of mixing on the decks. Getting his start in 1999 this artist is no rookie behind the turntables with his wide range of styles from tare-out/mash-up to melodic dubwise mixing. In 2006 he made his debut with his collaboration hit 'Another Champion' with long time producing partner Direct Feed on the label Hum Fi Drum.....|http://www.raggascum.com/|https://www.facebook.com/officialraggascum?fref=ts|★•´´¯`•AUDIO-ONE|(m.i.a. dnb norcal)|One of San Francisco's most musically diverse DJ’s making himself a staple in the notorious club and rave scenes for over a decade. DJ Audio1 digs deep with an eclectic mix of classics, new music, remixes and exclusive edits while showcasing his stellar programming, fast paced mixing and turntable skills. While his roots are in Hip-Hop, DJ Audio1 is better known as one of the top Drum&Bass/Dubstep DJs on the West Coast, affiliated to the MURDA IN AMERICA crew. |https://soundcloud.com/#audio1|https://www.facebook.com/thedjaudio1|★•´´¯`•SUBREAPER|(m.i.a. dnb boston)|Jeff 'Subreaper' has been defining his mix style since the turn of the millennium. With a solid dedication to the art form, Jeff secured slots performing at various venues along the east coast under, Marc Pastor, a name built from fragments of his name and interests.|Jeff devoted himself to growing as an artist through various means and methods. Taking on production in 2002, an alliance was formed with fellow Drum & Bass performer, Andromeda. The project resulted in 9 rough tracks that would cement a strong basis for future productions.|https://soundcloud.com/#subreaper|http://miadnb.com/profile.php?id=32|★•´´¯`•KRSP|(m.i.a. dnb kansas, Galactic Soul Tribe)|It started in the late 90's. I heard some Drum'n'Bass at some show I don't remember the name of. I didn't know it was drum'n'bass at the time, I just knew I had to get more of this NOW!!! M.I.A. CREW:

★•´´¯`• DANNY THE WILD CHILD
(compression san francisco / sound solution digital / rockers 175 / m.i.a. dnb chicago)

Danny the Wildchild aka Daniel Garcia was born on the South side of Chicago in 1977. The brother of a once aspiring DJ, he keenly watched and quickly learned the tricks of the trade. Danny began djing at age nine soon surpassing his brother’s abilities and eventually inherited his equipment and records. At twelve, Danny entered a Chicago area contest for young DJ’s and won. He took home that fifty-dollar prize and was called “The Wildchild” from that day forward.......
https://www.facebook.com/pages/Danny-The-Wildchild/115971325117979
http://soundcloud.com/danny-the-wildchild

★•´´¯`•ALFONZ "DELAMOTA"
(combat records / high $ociety / m.i.a. dnb chicago)

His name is synonymous with Chicago drum n bass and for being one of the founders and president of one of Americas largest drum n bass music groups, the M.I.A. (murda In america). DELAMOTA got his start djing the after-hours and small underground parties in Chicago during the early 90's rave scene as a dj, in 1998 he decided to start a production company called Sky High and put on several shows with attendance as high as 8500 people in a three room venue. With his dedication to the dnb sound he managed to travel all over the United States, Alfonz has played well over 25 cities in over 20 states both headlining and djing along side some of the worlds top electronic music producers and djs.
https://www.facebook.com/pages/Alfonz-DeLaMota/235722766465723
http://www.soundcloud.com/alfonzdelamota

★•´´¯`•RAGGA SCUM
(congo natty / cymbalism recordings / m.i.a. dnb kansas city)

Ragga Scum is widely known for his inhuman technical style of mixing on the decks. Getting his start in 1999 this artist is no rookie behind the turntables with his wide range of styles from tare-out/mash-up to melodic dubwise mixing. In 2006 he made his debut with his collaboration hit 'Another Champion' with long time producing partner Direct Feed on the label Hum Fi Drum.....
http://www.raggascum.com/
https://www.facebook.com/officialraggascum?fref=ts

★•´´¯`•AUDIO-ONE
(m.i.a. dnb norcal)

One of San Francisco's most musically diverse DJ’s making himself a staple in the notorious club and rave scenes for over a decade. DJ Audio1 digs deep with an eclectic mix of classics, new music, remixes and exclusive edits while showcasing his stellar programming, fast paced mixing and turntable skills. While his roots are in Hip-Hop, DJ Audio1 is better known as one of the top Drum&Bass/Dubstep DJs on the West Coast, affiliated to the MURDA IN AMERICA crew.
https://soundcloud.com/#audio1
https://www.facebook.com/thedjaudio1

★•´´¯`•SUBREAPER
(m.i.a. dnb boston)

Jeff 'Subreaper' has been defining his mix style since the turn of the millennium. With a solid dedication to the art form, Jeff secured slots performing at various venues along the east coast under, Marc Pastor, a name built from fragments of his name and interests.
Jeff devoted himself to growing as an artist through various means and methods. Taking on production in 2002, an alliance was formed with fellow Drum & Bass performer, Andromeda. The project resulted in 9 rough tracks that would cement a strong basis for future productions.
https://soundcloud.com/#subreaper
http://miadnb.com/profile.php?id=32

★•´´¯`•KRSP
(m.i.a. dnb kansas, Galactic Soul Tribe)
It started in the late 90's. I heard some Drum'n'Bass at some show I don't remember the name of. I didn't know it was drum'n'bass at the time, I just knew I had to get more of this NOW!!! It was that very next day I started in my search. I started coming up with some planet of the drum stuff. Then after that i moved right through the sub genres until I found Techstep. JeeYA!!!!
I started playing records about a decade ago. Really just got into it for me, I just wanted to hear what I could mix together in my room for me. My goal was never to be a superstar dj. Eventually after getting to the point of wanting to now share my music with people, I was ready.

RSVP.



This year’s Paste party at SXSW will be bigger than ever. Four days. Forty-four bands.


HGTV has teamed up with Paste for our ninth annual party in Austin, Texas, at SXSW, March 13-16. With 11 bands per day, the lineup includes both some of the festival’s most exciting veteran performers including Billy Bragg, Buddy Miller & Jim Lauderdale, Josh Ritter and The Zombies, as well as newcomers like Foxygen, The Lone Bellow and GUARDS.


Last year, HGTV and Paste paired together to find The New Sound of HGTV. Grand prize winner CR Smith, whose music has been regularly featured on the channel, will be playing the Austin event, as well.


The SXSW Official four-day party will be held at one of 6th Street’s biggest music venues, The Stage on Sixth (508 E.6th Street), from noon to 6pm.


Here are the acts booked so far (more announcements to come):

column14:
Artist rumored to be at SX. Do512 will update as soon as more details are available. To get the latest updates, be sure to follow "Sound City Players" on Do512!

via music-news.com:
"Dave Grohl has said in interviews that he will be showcasing his Sound City Players at SXSW next month and today John Fogerty let slip that he will be playing SXSW as well."
"A line at the end of a press release for the Fogerty album today mentioned 'John Fogerty will tour in 2013 and look for him to be at this year's SXSW in Austin (dates/events TBA).'"


via Brian Ives, Radio.com:
"Dave Grohl's Sound City Players blew the roof off of Park City Live in Utah earlier this month at the Sundance Film Festival (January 18), and they will rock the Hollywood Palladium after the film's L.A. premiere later this week. As of now, that is the only concert that the all-star group has on their schedule, but it looks like they might be hitting a few other locations, including New York and South by Southwest."

"If you’ve been under a rock for the past few weeks, the Sound City Players is a group put together by Grohl, and includes his fellow Foo Fighters, his Nirvana-mate Krist Novoselic, Corey Taylor, Rick Nielsen of Cheap Trick, Stevie Nicks, Rick Springfield and John Fogerty, among others. The huge collective are promoting Grohl’s film, Sound City, about the legendary Los Angeles recording studio. The film opens on Thursday (January 31) in select theaters, and will be available for download from iTunes on Friday (February 1). The soundtrack, which features collaborations between Grohl and a number of artists including Nicks, Springfield and Paul McCartney, will be available in March."



Article: kroq.cbslocal.com

column2: Fashionext.org presents: Fashionext Lounge
column13: Going to SxSW? Come out on Sunday March 10th to check out all the latest in tech and fashion, while enjoying a bite to eat and a drink on us! Taking place during the 2013 South by Southwest Conference (SxSW) in Austin, Texas, the Fashionext Lounge is a pioneering event that will provide a platform to exchange ideas on the future of fashion through the innovation lens.|On March 10, 2013, our event will bring together outstanding emerging designers, fashion tech startups, established brands, investors, fashion influencers and global customers at the SxSW Conference. Alongside traditional fashion designers showcasing at the lounge, our showcase will also include eco, sustainable, ethical and fair-trade designers who are reshaping the concept of consumerism. Our event will act as a catalyst in promoting innovation in fashion to a distinctive and large global film, music, and interactive technology audience.
column14:
Going to SxSW? Come out on Sunday March 10th to check out all the latest in tech and fashion, while enjoying a bite to eat and a drink on us!

Taking place during the 2013 South by Southwest Conference (SxSW) in Austin, Texas, the Fashionext Lounge is a pioneering event that will provide a platform to exchange ideas on the future of fashion through the innovation lens.


On March 10, 2013, our event will bring together outstanding emerging designers, fashion tech startups, established brands, investors, fashion influencers and global customers at the SxSW Conference. Alongside traditional fashion designers showcasing at the lounge, our showcase will also include eco, sustainable, ethical and fair-trade designers who are reshaping the concept of consumerism. Our event will act as a catalyst in promoting innovation in fashion to a distinctive and large global film, music, and interactive technology audience.

column2: North of 41 Lounge
column13: The North of 41 Lounge is back for our annual event atSxSW Interactive. This year is going to be better than ever! We have a ton of activities that are planned for you in Austin on Saturday and Sunday March 9th & 10th, 2013. We are located at 309 E. 3rd St. @ Fogo de Chao (corner of 3rd and Trinity). We are 100 ft from the front doors of the convention center!!!We will be doing various product giveaways all weekend. We will be hosting a number of parties throughout the weekend. There will also be a couple of panel discussions taking place starting right after lunch on Sat., March 10th. Make sure to stop in at the North of 41 Lounge to charge up your laptop and grab a drink with friends. We have plenty of space for meetings and while you are in the venue, check out the companies who are displaying at the lounge. The North of 41 Lounge also has FREE WiFi access along with our VIP Blogger Lounge. When you need a spot to relax in between the panels, stop in and see us. Make sure to follow us on Twitter for the latest updates. @northof41 We look forward to seeing you in Austin at North of 41 . To contact us, email: info@northof41.org

A Mid West Festival + Unofficial Showcase Event during SX in Austin, TX March 12th - 17th, 2013.

This is an Unofficial SXSW Event and brought to you by BSHR Entertainment and Sponsored by Music Saves Lives


THE VENUE

The Firehouse Lounge features classically prepared cocktails, delectable accompaniments, an inviting atmosphere, and a variety of live music. Elevate your experience at Downtown's NEWEST venue.


FEATURING. . .

The giftbags will be given out at the VIP Dinner Party and the Main Event. Mini Moo Business Cards will contain download codes for guests to return home and enter for more goodies!


Plus play the Indie Band Drinking Game + Sky Scavenger Hunt all week to win Sponsored Prize Packages!

THE [SOS] SCHEDULE of SHOWS

Tuesday 3/12 Welcome to Austin: A Singer/Songwriter Party + Evening Events


Wednesday 3/13 Rockin’ Zombie Luau Day Party + Evening Events


Thursday 3/14 The Calm Before the Storm Day Party and the VIP Dinner + Cocktail Party+ evening events.

Mini spa treatments, an art gala with VIP Dinner + Cocktail party.

Friday 3/15 Blue Sky on Broadway + The Indie Dance Party: Bring on the Weekend

The start of the Vinyl Record Club in Partnership with Broadway Recording Company.


Saturday 3/16 BSHR’s “Giant” Launch Party

The main event complete with miniature EVERYTHING. Guests receive The “Grow it @ Home” Giftbag. Raffles of various prizes and giveaways.


Sunday 3/17 The Green Giant Party + Closing events

column2: #VegasTech Community presents: #VegasTech SXSW Lounge
column13: Bringing the style of old-school Vegas to Austin in 2013. Come enjoy a hosted bar and appetizers served in an intimate venue at 222 6th St. Mix and mingle with key players in the Vegas tech scene and learn why Slate Magazine said it has the potential to be the next "innovation cluster" in the coming year. Event details:When: Sunday, March 10th, 2013 at 5:00 p.m.Where: 2nd Floor of 222 East 6th Street, Austin, TX 78701 What: An open bar and networking event with SXSW attendeesPrice: Free with a SXSW badge (must be 21+ years old to enter)

column2: THE Entrepreneur Experience at SXSW (+ Party List & ATC Services)
column6: 500 East Cesar Chavez Street, Austin, TX, 78701
column13: THE Entrepreneur Experience at SXSW The problem: You're at SXSW right now and have zero idea what to do or where to go next. Standing in line sucks - - you KNOW that you could be doing something better... but what?! The solution: Get in the know right now about the best entrepreneur events. You came to SXSW in the hopes of helping your business. You are asinine if you don't get a 10x ROI on your SXSW investment. Asse9, Austin Secret Society of Entrepreneurs, thinks it's asinine if you spend money without getting back your money ASAP. You're also dumb if you don't get access to awesome mentors via networking events. I talk about both mentors and networking in chapters five and four (respectively) of my book, "What They Don't Teach You At Stanford Business School". Last year, SXSW was a whirlwind of activities that had an entrepreneurial bent to them but many entrepreneurs were left in the cold. First timers have it the hardest. My goal is to be your ROI within 2 hours of handing over your hard earned cash. ************** "SXSW has one of the best tech conference bangs for the buck" - Larry Chiang ************** This SXSW Party list is just for entrepreneurs. It is party summary information on South by Southwest events that get delivered to you via a password locked file. If ROI is NOT your focus, leave now. If you don't trust this money-back-offer, leave NOW. If you can't read FINE PRINT THAT SAYS IT IS FREE IF YOU TAKE A PICTURE OF YOUR FACE NEXT TO YOUR BADGE, leave now. For a few of you that have an existing, VC funded company, read on... **The VIP SXSW Entrepreneurial Experience*** The VIP SXSW EE compiles the best of the best SXSW events for funded entrepreneurs. This VIP, SXSW-EE, offer includes: - Private, marquee networking events with VCs. - Multiple up to the second updates emailed or texted to your PDA / smart phone. - Confirmed RSVP to events (worth over $700 alone as of 11:11am Feb 10) - Names of event publicists, planners and hosts so you have a higher likelihood to successfully guestlist I have gathered host names, locations and party information of SXSW events and get them delivered to you via a password locked file. Yes, it has a money-back guarantee ************** "I love migrating myself from the waitlist to VIP. It's what they don't teach you in b-school" - Larry Chiang ************** If you'd like a discount code, tweet this NOW "Want the VIP experience @sxsw?! RT http://bit.ly/buster12" and follow @larrychiang. I will DM you the code via Twitter I enjoyed meeting you and mentoring you. I look forward to listening and learning from you and about you. Keep seeking out your ROI here at SXSW and I look forward to saying hi in person. Find me please! I am the 6' 5" Chinese dude sporting a tie and wearing outlet mall khakis. Tsia Jian y'all! Larry Chiang P.S. MBAs are welcome. I will single handedly get you ROI for one year's tuition with the MBA experience. Give me just two days at Austin and $189 of your moo-lah. P.P.S. MBAs only... here is a video for you http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fFt2cX99hiw P.P.P.S. And for reading all the way down a surprise bonus: Thirteen free support emails with Larry Chiang before SXSW even starts so you will absolutely ace 2013 SXSW

column14:
HT Staffing
presents
First Annual Give-Back Party Benefiting Dress for Success Austin


It’s time for SXSW® again, and to celebrate we are throwing our first annual give-back party at Russian House of Austin, one on Austin's newest hot spots, on March 8 from 5:30pm to 7:30pm to benefit Dress for Success Austin. Come join us and the best of the best in the local HR and recruiting community to help a worthy cause—while networking and enjoying live music from The Flying Balalaika Brothers in one of Austin’s hot spots! Register today to attend, donate or sponsor! Two free drink tokens will be given to all registered attendees upon entry.


Established in 2003, Dress for Success Austin is a non-profit organization that promotes the economic independence of disadvantaged women by providing professional attire, a network of support and career development tools to help women thrive in work and in life. Dress for Success Austin has helped over 7,000 disadvantaged women get back on their feet and become productive members of society. This wonderful organization completely depends on voluntary donations from the community to make their work possible. All proceeds (100%) raised from HT Staffing through donations and sponsorships will be given to Dress for Success Austin. Suggested donations include cash, handbags, unopened makeup, or gift cards (MC/Visa, Amex, Target, Walmart, Marshall’s TJ Maxx, gas). Note: Donations are not required to attend, but are encouraged.


The Flying Balalaika Brothers formed by Russian-Ukrainian musicians who moved to the United States in 1994 and have toured America since 1996. Recently the FBB's have released a new CD called Op, Op, Romale, loosely translated as "Hey, Hey, Gypsy people". The album incorporates humor into a mix of Russian, Romani-Gypsy, and American music. Pair great music with the finest authentic dishes Russian House of Austin has to offer, prepared by the award- winning executive chef Vladimir Gribkov whose specialties include homemade classic Russian such as Pelmeni, soups as Borsch and Solyanka. Enjoy one of 25 different infused vodkas made with the finest Russian vodka.


If you are interested in becoming a sponsor, please call Mark Turpin at (512) 533-9700.

Sponsorship opportunities are available now. RSVPs for attendees will open in February. For additional event information, please visit www.nytm.org.|-- found online @http://nytm.org/blog/entry/13-17-2013/made-in-ny-austin-returns-to-sxsw-to-celebrate-nyc-tech-cultur...
column14:
Visit MadeinNYaustin.com for more details...

Made in NY: Austin, an event being presented by NY Tech Meetup, the City of New York, and Gust as well as a wide range of New York-based technology startups, will return to SXSW on Sunday, March 9, 2013, from 9 a.m. to 2 a.m. at the newly-remodeled AMOA-Arthouse at the Jones Center in Austin, Texas. The event, expected to attract over 2,000 attendees, will celebrate the vast resources, diverse talent, and unique cultural inspiration of New York tech, culture, food, film, art and music.


Jessica Lawrence, Managing Director of NY Tech Meetup said, “Last year’s event was such a huge success for the entire NYC start-up community and everyone who attended. We’re looking forward to expanding this showcase of the outstanding people and ideas that help make NYC one of the best places to start, build, and expand a business.”


Katherine Oliver, Commissioner of the Mayor’s Office of Media and Entertainment, said, “New York City is a thriving center of creativity, from the surge of films and television shows produced here to the growth of digital startups based in the City that are reinventing the way we live our lives. New York City has so much to offer, and we’re thrilled to be able to showcase the many talented New Yorkers who will be a part of Made in NY: Austin.”

Rachel Haot, Chief Digital Officer of New York City said, “The City of New York is home to not only the world’s most innovative tech minds and businesses but also those on the forefront of art, culture, and food. We’re ecstatic to work with NY Tech Meetup to make this a true New York experience in Austin, and it’s sure to be a blast.”


David Rose, CEO of Gust said: “It’s going to be great to be back in Austin to repeat the amazing showcase of New York’s tech industry that took place last year. Gust has continued to power deal flow management tools and investor relations for NYC-area startups, venture funds, and angel groups, and we can’t wait to do it again at Made in NY: Austin.”


Last year’s event, which featured more than 45 New York tech startups, received outstanding reviews from over 1,000 attendees (with another 2,000 on the waiting list). While sponsors for the event are still being confirmed, previous sponsors include Buddy Media, Wilson Sonsini Goodrich & Rosati, DFJ Gotham Ventures, Shapeways, Rapp, Etsy, and Tumblr.


The all-day and evening event will include interactive and experiential installations of New York’s best technology along with pitch sessions, workshops, and a high-tech, high-energy party to cap off the night. The state-of-the-art venue will also include the popular arts+tech interactive #FEED installations, powered by Twitter.


The event is free and open to the public but does require an RSVP. Sponsorship opportunities are available now. RSVPs for attendees will open in February. For additional event information, please visit www.nytm.org.


-- found online @http://nytm.org/blog/entry/13-17-2013/made-in-ny-austin-returns-to-sxsw-to-celebrate-nyc-tech-cultur...

column14:
Connect with Austin's most successful entrepreneurs, most active angel investors, most experienced lawyers, and most prominent venture capitalists for another Epic Office Hours!

Interested in moving your startup to Austin?
This is your chance to meet the mover's and shakers of the Austin scene.


Interested in learning more about Capital Factory?
There will be many Capital Factory Mentors available to meet with and you can tour our incredible facilities.

How does it work?

  1. Register on Eventbrite
  2. A week before the event we will schedule your meetings
  3. During the event you will get 20 minutes with each Mentor

How can you make the most of your 20 minutes?

  • Don't spend more than 5 minutes introducing yourself and explaining your business
  • Give short, concise answers to the Mentor's questions
  • If you're doing all the talking, you're not learning anything
  • Come prepared - research who you are meeting with on LinkedIn and write down questions in advance
  • Send a 1 page overview of your company or <5 min video for the Mentor to review in advance
Who will be there?
Last time we had Mentors from:
  • Austin Technology Incubator (incubator)
  • Austin Ventures (vc)
  • Capital Factory Mentors (incubator)
  • Central Texas Angel Network (angel)
  • DreamIt Ventures (incubator)
  • G-51 (vc)
  • Kastner, Huggins, Reddien & Gravelle (legal)
  • Silverton Partners (vc)
  • TechStars Cloud (incubator)
  • and many more...

* this event is not affiliated with SXSW

column2: Carnegie Mellon University and the Pittsburgh Technology Council present: Pittsburgh Innovation Party
column13: Going to SXSW Interactive? So are we! Come out and join our party!The Pittsburgh Technology Council’s Creative Tech Network is seeking innovative projects, partners and sponsors for the 2013 Pittsburgh Innovation Party, an official SXSW event at SXSW Interactive +Film in downtown Austin, Texas.EVENT DATE: Saturday, March 9, 2013 8pm-2am|Presented by Carnegie Mellon University and the Pittsburgh Technology Council|Lead Sponsors: CMU’s Heinz College and Human Computer Interaction Institute|Supporting Sponsors: Alpha Lab, The Entertainment Technology Center, Steeltown Entertainment, CMU University Advancement|Supported by the Claude Worthington Benedum Foundation and the SPARK Kids & Creativity Network|An incubator of cutting-edge technologies, the SXSW Interactive and Film Festival features five days of presentations from the brightest minds in technology and scores of exciting networking events hosted by industry leaders. From creative workshops to big-picture analysis of the future, SXSW Interactive has become the place to experience a preview of what is unfolding in the world of innovation. The Pittsburgh Innovation Event will be an official SXSW-sponsored event, held in downtown Austin during SXSW Interactive + Film, in the heart of the SXSW conference. As an official SXSW event, our event will be promoted through SXSW official marketing channels to over 40,000 attendees.|The event, which will be open to all SXSW Interactive + Film badge-holders, event partners and VIPs, will feature a full evening of SXSW-style mixing and mingling including: an exclusive VIP pre-party with national investors, celebrities and Pittsburgh innovators; an interactive arcade with the newest projects from Pittsburgh companies and students; live VJ, with music and video remixes of Pittsburgh’s innovation successes, and a circulation of up to 30,000 national and international conference attendees. Because SXSW is the preeminent event for business and technology innovation, the conference is the ideal place to raise awareness of Pittsburgh’s innovation – and reinvention, as well as reinforce the opportunities which exist and are promulgating in this region. This year’s SXSW Film and Interactive event is slated to attract over 40,000 conference-goers.|There are many ways to get involved! If you are interested in joining the fun, email Kim Harvey at kharvey@pghtech.org by January 15.
column14:
Going to SXSW Interactive? So are we! Come out and join our party!

The Pittsburgh Technology Council’s Creative Tech Network is seeking innovative projects, partners and sponsors for the 2013 Pittsburgh Innovation Party, an official SXSW event at SXSW Interactive +Film in downtown Austin, Texas.

EVENT DATE: Saturday, March 9, 2013 8pm-2am

Presented by Carnegie Mellon University and the Pittsburgh Technology Council


Lead Sponsors: CMU’s Heinz College and Human Computer Interaction Institute


Supporting Sponsors: Alpha Lab, The Entertainment Technology Center, Steeltown Entertainment, CMU University Advancement


Supported by the Claude Worthington Benedum Foundation and the SPARK Kids & Creativity Network


An incubator of cutting-edge technologies, the SXSW Interactive and Film Festival features five days of presentations from the brightest minds in technology and scores of exciting networking events hosted by industry leaders. From creative workshops to big-picture analysis of the future, SXSW Interactive has become the place to experience a preview of what is unfolding in the world of innovation. The Pittsburgh Innovation Event will be an official SXSW-sponsored event, held in downtown Austin during SXSW Interactive + Film, in the heart of the SXSW conference. As an official SXSW event, our event will be promoted through SXSW official marketing channels to over 40,000 attendees.


The event, which will be open to all SXSW Interactive + Film badge-holders, event partners and VIPs, will feature a full evening of SXSW-style mixing and mingling including: an exclusive VIP pre-party with national investors, celebrities and Pittsburgh innovators; an interactive arcade with the newest projects from Pittsburgh companies and students; live VJ, with music and video remixes of Pittsburgh’s innovation successes, and a circulation of up to 30,000 national and international conference attendees. Because SXSW is the preeminent event for business and technology innovation, the conference is the ideal place to raise awareness of Pittsburgh’s innovation – and reinvention, as well as reinforce the opportunities which exist and are promulgating in this region. This year’s SXSW Film and Interactive event is slated to attract over 40,000 conference-goers.


There are many ways to get involved! If you are interested in joining the fun, email Kim Harvey at kharvey@pghtech.org by January 15.

column2: Nest Suomi@SXSW2013
column6: 500 East Cesar Chavez Street, Austin, TX, 78701
column13: Suomi goes to SXSW 2013 as NEST booth at the Trade Show. Join in to our merry crew of startup entrepreneurs. We have accommodation. We have Trade Show booth. We have Interactive or Platinum badges. We have Mobile Monday. We have tons of parties to go to. We have seminars. We have BBQ. We can have it all. The 2nd batch of SXSW registrations opened, open until Feb 8 (one month before the event) or until we run out of space at our ClubHouse and/or our booth. However, January 18th is the deadline for all the materials and participating company information under the Nest Helsinki booth, so if for Startup or Business pack, be sure to act before that! Questions - get in touch, details below! /Peter ***************************************************************************** SXSW®, South by Southwest®, is happening again in March, 2013 (8th-17th) in Austin, Texas Peter Green from MobileSensing/GreenFly Events is taking Finnish startups over to Austin again next year, for the fourth time. Double booth and accommodation for the first ones (approx 30 peeps) confirmed. Flights are not included, but pretty much everything else is. More to come when needed. Few words about the SXSW and then to the packages: (Note, if viewing this on iPad/mobile device, the price shown is with Finnish VAT included) SXSW® offers the unique convergence of original music, independent films, and emerging technologies. Fostering creative and professional growth alike, SXSW® is the premier destination for discovery. The SXSWi, South by Southwest Interactive, will be organized for 20th time (SXSW music festival for the 27th time). The Interactive part is between March 8-12 and Music between 12-17. Film goes on all the time. Earlier this year Peter Green (original FinnMobster since 2009) had over 20 startups going to the event of close to 50.000 attendees, with a SXSW Trade Show booth (among about 300 other exhibitors). Many of us were also staying at a group accommodation at the FinnMob Clubhouse. 2013 will be the fourth SXSW organized by Peter, this again bigger and better than before, in 2010 we had about 10 Finns over to SXSW, in 2011 about 50. This year there were close to 100 - and according to the booth pitch the aim in 2013 is 200 companies. So, we are doing a share towards that 200 right here! Join in to Suomi @SXSW2013 crew - let's make sure there will be the 200 Finns this time (and maybe few Swedes with us, too:) The packages are planned to suite well for start-ups, and includes either Interactive or Platinum (withMusic and Film) badge, Group accommodation in a SuomiSXSW Clubhouse (beers and breakfast available; B&B&B:), Trade Show booth/stand as a "homebase" during the Interactive part (Trade Show deom Sunday 10th until Wednesday 13th). Also various side events are being planned (with sponsorship and visibility for Startup packs and especially Business packs). For the Business Pack there is also possibility to use a local PR agency for press releases and press tours during the Trade Show as well as Promotions by a professional promotion company. These packs (and specific prices) will be specified later (sorry about that!) These package prices are valid until end of November (sorry, could not stretch the deadlines more) and there's a maximum quantity of 20 Evangelist-, 20 Startups- and 10 Business- packs at this stage. But yes, the aim is the 200, so this will be extendable, with more houses, RV's and extended booth space if demand exceeds the supply. The packages are explained underneath the selections above, please note that for the evangelist pack there's only one person per company allowed. Also, there is a good opportunity to make this SuomiSXSW 2013 event as part of TEM support (Finnish Ministry of Employment anf the Economy) program for Finnish export. If so, there will be an approximate 40-50% refund of all the event related travel- and marketing expenditures afterwards, including the package price, travel and other direct costs. Possible restrictions for companies enjoying some other benefits will be clarified asap. The accommodation will be available from Thursday March 7th until Sunday March 17th. The accommodations (beds) will be given out on a first come first in beds -basis. However the aim is to have a place to sleep, indoors, for everyone. The house is big, there's another one smaller on the same lot, and possibly space for 9 sleeper RV's (motorhomes) as well. The accommodation is on the 1st Street, about 5 Miles from downtown, with direct bus connection and about 10 mins, 10 $s taxi drive away. If you have either accommodation or badge sorted out, contact me and let's sort it out. Also, let's negotiate If you have both, but want to hang with our crew at the Trade Show and side events. In case of not getting enough participants (into this totally awesome event) we reserve the right to cancel the trip and reservations, and will return the paid amount in full (yes, covering the service fees too) /Peter peter.green(a)sensing.fi +358405707911 P.S. We are also looking for event partners, sponsors, with extra visibility in all materials and possibilities to involve audiences, both the event crew (Finnish startups) as well as other audiences. Please contact and let's be creative and plan ahead. Price for sponsoring is 3.500€, or supporting services for the SuomiSXSW crew for the value. Sponsoring includes a Platinum ticket and accommodation as well as logos in all the publications (so a little like Business Pack in a way).

column14:
Welcome to Austin and welcome to SXSW Interactive!


As the kick off event – the evening offers the perfect networking opportunity to renew connections and sync up itineraries for the weekend. We will have free-flowing libations and serve a Texas inspired hors d’ oeuvres menu.


The evening will also feature the presentation of the BiT Top Ten Innovator Awards recognizing the top ten African Americans who made the biggest impact in 2012. And you can’t experience the Live Music Capital Music of the World™ without live music – right? We’ll have a sizzling live soul auditory experience for your pleasure – along with DJ Phife spinning the best in eclectic neo-sounds.


This is a free event, no SXSW badge is required.



Click here for directions to the Carver Museum.


TheTop 10 Black Innovators of 2012 Awards will be presented as a component of the SXSW Interactive Festival on Friday, March 8, 2013 during the BiT Welcome Reception being held from 6 p.m. to 9 p.m. at The Carver Museum.

We are currently accepting nominees until Sunday, January 27th – stay tuned for the winners.

column14:
MEOW and WIMPS

cordially invite all professional women in music to attend an exclusive March event – our Second Annual:

High Tea Ladies Luncheon at SXSW

Friday, March 15, 2013

11:30 AM – 1:30 PM

Chateau Bellevue

708 San Antonio Street

Austin, TX 78701

$25 per person includes luncheon, dessert, beverages, tax and gratuity

Chateau Bellevue is an elegant Victorian mansion built in 1874 and a historic downtown Austin landmark. It is home to the Austin Women’s Club.

Wear something *sparkly* and bring your promo materials to pass around.

MEOW (Musicians for Equal Opportunities) is the brainchild of ROCKRGRL Magazine founder Carla Desantis Black. MEOW's mission is to "level the playing field" for women in music through networking, education and advocacy. www.meowonline.org

WIMPS (Women in Music Professional Society) is an informal monthly networking lunch group founded in 2007.


The Fine Print: You must RSVP and pay in advance by March first via Eventbrite and PayPal. No refunds. This luncheon is for ladies only and is not an official SXSW event.


SPONSORSHIP OPPORTUNITIES AVAILABLE


We will be giving away goodie bags to our 120 attendees. For $75 we will include your promo, CD, business card - whatever!


Need more information? E-mail info@meowonline.org or call 512.363.5345.

column14:
Tech Career Expo is the premier job fair showcasing the best tech jobs and career opportunities available. This is the ideal place for you to meet with and discuss employment with top companies – from startups to large firms – in a casual, creative environment (Rivals Steakhouse).

Professionals involved in all aspects of technology (from engineering, programming and design, to marketing, sales, management and more) are welcome to participate.

Tech Career Expo is free to attend to both SXSW attendees and non-attendees. We are open from 11am to 5pm, Friday, March 8 and 11pm to 5pm on Saturday, March 9th.

We look forward to seeing you at the Rivals Steakhouse, on the corner of 5th and Trinity Street, one block from the Convention Center. Copyright © 2003-2012 Engage Digital. All rights reserved.

column2: SXSW Eco & Geostellar Launch Party
column13: Join SXSW Eco and Geostellar to celebrate the launch of two forward thinking enterprises! SXSW Eco is excited to launch our 2013 season and envision the future: moving beyond sustainability and pioneering deliberate, progressive, and restorative systems worldwide. Meet the Eco team, learn about our action oriented program and submit your ideas through our PanelPicker submission platform, now open! Help us launch tech startup Geostellar as they bring together communities to better understand the potential of renewable energy, and how to put it into action today. A company based on simplicity, science and success, Geostellar helps consumers understand the value of solar energy and empowers them to play a role in the clean tech economy.

column14:
&


presents

Doing Business in the USA

Friday 8th March - 9.30am - 5pm - Austin, Texas


Doing Business in the USA is the essential conference for Founders, CEOs and C-level executives planning to enter or expand their business in North America.

What’s in the Programme

  • Keynotes: leading experts’ give their take on the challenges and opportunities for international firms looking to crack the US market
  • Business Development - understanding US business culture, building relationships and business, from small firms to major corporates
  • Keeping legal and tax efficient - the run-down of IP, staffing, avoiding litigation, incorporation, shares and tax
  • Industry Trends - taken from a new business perspective, a run-down of the digital sector in the US with a look at potential opportunities and emerging trends
  • Immigration - understand the visa landscape, the options, costs, obligations and obstacles
  • Case Studies - the warts’n’all reality of setting up in the US, tips, tricks and workarounds, the pitfalls and possibilities
  • Geography Lessons - the US is a big place with lots of regional variation: gain insight on the digital scene in Silicon Valley, Silicon Alley and points inbetween
  • Investment - get the lowdown on what makes US VCs and angels tick, discover how US investors approach overseas investment

What You Will Learn

  • How to win new business
  • Understanding US business culture
  • Understanding and securing funding
  • Building partnerships, networks and connections
  • Staying legal and tax compliant
  • Protecting intellectual property
  • Hiring, firing and office logistics
  • Understand where to open an office
  • Discovering regional and state support and incentives
  • Meeting fellow international SXSW delegates
  • Networking with potential partners/collaborators

Get Involved

If you’re interested in speaking or exhibiting at the Doing Business in the USA event, please drop us a line with a little bio information and what topic you’d cover. Media partnerships are most welcome, please contact us for more information.


Questions Questions...

If you have any questions about the Doing Business in the USA Mastercalss please do get in touch...

column14:
Artist rumored to be at SX2013. We think Operation Every Band might just be onto something here...


On March 12, "We are a Sad Band" is playing at The Main according to the official SX schedule BUT no band with that name seems to exist. Here's Operation Every Band's reasoning that it's ACTUALLY Thom Yorke:

Every year, there seems to be something that doesn’t quite look right on the SXSW roster. Many times, this ends up being a surprise show of some sort, an event many know takes place all over Austin. After looking through Spotify, I’ll normally hit Google to begin my research. We Are a Sad Band, who are apparently a funk band from “Sadville” , Texas (their website is listed as http://sxsw.com), came up with zero online references and currently sits alone on the schedule for Tuesday night at The Main...

Nate Headden, OEB writer and resident sleuth, put together a solid case that We Are A Sad Band is none other than Thom Yoke’s Atoms for Peace. Again, this is purely a rumor at this point, but some interesting notes:
- If this is a secret show, then the artist would have to be a pretty big name to necessitate a non-listed showcase, especially off the official SXSW roster.
- We Are A Sad Band has a tongue-in-cheek tone to it. Who would be a band that may be hastily called a “sad band” by press? Radiohead ended up being the first name we called out.
- A secret SXSW showcase would normally coincide with a major release. Radiohead hasn’t been in the studio, but Yorke’s Atoms For Peace is releasing AMOK next week.
- Yorke and Nigel Godrich recently inferred there will be some tour dates coming soon in a Reddit “Ask Me Anything” session this week.
- And our smoking gun. While AMOK is being released next week, a 12” is set to follow in the UK on March 11, which would mean a US release should coincide with March 12, the day of the showcase. Not only that, the 12” will also contain a non-album B-side. The name of the B-side: SAD.



Do512 will keep you up to date! Follow "Thom Yorke and Atoms for Peace" on Do512...

Each day will begin with panel discussions, workshops, and demos, and round out with the opportunity for registrants to tinker with a pavilion of products.

The event takes place from Saturday, March 9 - Tuesday, March 12, 2013, at the InterContinental Stephen F. Austin Hotel, Capital Ballroom, Section B.


The daily schedule is as follows:

11:00 AM - Panel Discussion
12:30 PM - Workshop/Hands-on Session
2:00 PM-6:00 PM - Demo Pavilion


Programming details will follow, and will be announced on this page and at sxsw.com/film. To participate in the event, register for a badge now - head to sxsw.com/attend to find out how.


To learn more about opportunities to participate at Come & Capture Film Factory please contact Sara Barney at sara@sxsw.com.

column2: The Social Revolución at SXSWi
column13: Oye Mi Canto - Listen to my Cry|It’s the exclamation of The Social Revolución: an interactive movement of Latinos using social media as their platform to create change. Through hashtags, pixels, or live updates, these ambitious individuals have used social media to spread ideas, foster communities and inspire a worldwide audience into action. PREMIERING AS THE OFFICIAL LATINO EVENT AT SXSW INTERACTIVE, THE SOCIAL REVOLUCIÓN WILL RECOGNIZE AND CELEBRATE THESE ONLINE CRIES HAPPENING IN CURRENT CULTURAL SHIFTS AND TRENDS, INTERNATIONAL AND LOCAL CAUSES, AND THROUGH THE MONUMENTAL VISIONS OF INDIVIDUALS. So let it be heard, let it be no longer ignored - Oye el canto of The Social Revolución.
column14:
Oye Mi Canto - Listen to my Cry

It’s the exclamation of The Social Revolución: an interactive movement of Latinos using social media as their platform to create change. Through hashtags, pixels, or live updates, these ambitious individuals have used social media to spread ideas, foster communities and inspire a worldwide audience into action. PREMIERING AS THE OFFICIAL LATINO EVENT AT SXSW INTERACTIVE, THE SOCIAL REVOLUCIÓN WILL RECOGNIZE AND CELEBRATE THESE ONLINE CRIES HAPPENING IN CURRENT CULTURAL SHIFTS AND TRENDS, INTERNATIONAL AND LOCAL CAUSES, AND THROUGH THE MONUMENTAL VISIONS OF INDIVIDUALS. So let it be heard, let it be no longer ignored - Oye el canto of The Social Revolución.

column2: Blacks in Tech and The Red Pump Project present: Rock The Red
column13: BiT and The Red Pump Project present Rock The Red|Every 47 minutes, a woman tests positive for HIV/AIDS in the United States. This is just one of many statistics which illustrate the growing impact of HIV/AIDS among women. It is also the reason why The Red Pump Project, a national HIV/AIDS awareness organization, was inspired to launch its fifth annual Rock the Red Pump® campaign.|BiT and The Red Pump Project invites you to join us as we Rock The Red on Sunday, March 10, 2013 from 4-6pm in the BiT House during SXSW. Join us for a fantastic afternoon where we bring together social justice and fashion to Rock the RED BOLDLY, FASHIONABLY while being AWAREof the impact of HIV/AIDS on our community. Red Pump will coordinate five simultaneous events around March 10 to commemorate NWGHAAD in Austin, Charlotte, Atlanta, New York, and Washington, D.C.|In Austin – we will be joined by the co-founder of the Red Pump Project, Luvvie Ajayi. ”Our goal is to normalize conversation about HIV/AIDS, and we choose to use red shoes to do it because they immediately grab your attention,” says Ajayi. “While we have people’s attention, let’s talk about AIDS!” Visit the Red Pump Project on Facebook for more information on how you can support and get involved in your area.
column14:
BiT and The Red Pump Project present Rock The Red


Every 47 minutes, a woman tests positive for HIV/AIDS in the United States. This is just one of many statistics which illustrate the growing impact of HIV/AIDS among women. It is also the reason why The Red Pump Project, a national HIV/AIDS awareness organization, was inspired to launch its fifth annual Rock the Red Pump® campaign.


BiT and The Red Pump Project invites you to join us as we Rock The Red on Sunday, March 10, 2013 from 4-6pm in the BiT House during SXSW. Join us for a fantastic afternoon where we bring together social justice and fashion to Rock the RED BOLDLY, FASHIONABLY while being AWAREof the impact of HIV/AIDS on our community. Red Pump will coordinate five simultaneous events around March 10 to commemorate NWGHAAD in Austin, Charlotte, Atlanta, New York, and Washington, D.C.


In Austin – we will be joined by the co-founder of the Red Pump Project, Luvvie Ajayi. ”Our goal is to normalize conversation about HIV/AIDS, and we choose to use red shoes to do it because they immediately grab your attention,” says Ajayi. “While we have people’s attention, let’s talk about AIDS!” Visit the Red Pump Project on Facebook for more information on how you can support and get involved in your area.

column14:
What? A hackathon for the black tech community at SXSW

Where?BiT House- SXSW

Why? We're bringing together the hacker/designer/founder community to design mobile and web applications for the film and music industry.

What’s in it for you?

· Network with the #blacktech community from across the country

· Create gorgeous new apps for film and music

· Eat amazing food all night plus brunch on Sunday morning!

· Make the most of your SXSW experience

· Share your resume with startups and corporations who are on the lookout for amazing talent

Best of all? Tickets are free!

For more information visit BlackGirlsHack.com,

follow us at @blackgirlshack or

email pr@blackgirlshack.com.

Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!


March 8th - 14th
Emo’s East Plaza
2015 E Riverside
(Between Emo’s East and the Beauty Ballroom)

We're elated to present 100 films, including featured premieres, 18 films that have won Best Feature, Best Documentary or Best Short at Film ExChange Network Festivals in Victoria, TX; Brooklyn, NY; New Orleans, LA; Corpus Christi, TX; Hamburg, Germany; and Lahti, Finland.

Highlights & Special Events: 100 Films, Superior Cinephile Contest, Unlimited Libations, Celebrity Appearances, Late Late Thursday Night Social Ride After Party, Special Event Premiere of Danko Jones (Lemmy Kilmister, Elijah Wood, Selma Blair, & Mike Watt), and NO BADGES/WRISTBANDS REQUIRED.

One film from each category will travel to the Victoria, TX Independent Film Festival, held April 4-7 2013, to compete for cash prizes totaling $5,000. As always Rxsm is FREE!

Unlimited complimentary libations during the entire 7 days thanks to the support of our sponsors: Revel Stoke Whiskey, UV Vodka, Tecate, Treaty Oak Rum, Waterloo Gin, Zico Water, Montana Cans, Cervexa Indio,Slacker Magazine, and Red River Noise.

column2: RUMOR - Rob Zombie at SX2013!

column14:
Artist rumored to be at SX2013.

Zombie's new horror The Lords of Salem will be making its U.S. Premiere as a Midnighter at SX2013. Can we expect a show as well? He released his most recent album, Mondo Sex Head, last year before co-headlining the "Twins of Evil" tour with Marilyn Manson. We think the last lines of this interview with Rolling Stone from September are pretty telling!

Do512 will update as soon as more details are available. To get the latest updates, be sure to follow "Rob Zombie" on Do512!

column2: Oklahoma Soundcheck
column13: Start the opening day of SXSW Music at Oklahoma’s Buffalo Lounge (located at 512). column14:
The Ideas Are Worthless conference is a forum to connect, educate, and inspire every attendee towards execution. Hosted by Black Founders and BiTHouse, the Austin conference is the perfect way to kick off your trip to SXSW Interactive and for local Austin entrepreneurs to learn from their peers in the Austin entrepreneur community and beyond.

A limited number of free tickets will be available to SXSW badge holders.

The conference will bring together diverse perspectives on tech entrepreneurship, while providing a platform for emerging companies, entrepreneurs, and investors to connect and take action.

Watch this video from the NYC Conference to see what to expect for the Austin Conference.

The program will include panelists, (including investors, CEOs, entrepreneurs, engineers), sharing insights into startup fundraising, investment strategies, running a company, new startup trends, and finding technical talent for your startup. The following will also be a part of the conference.

Startup Clinic. The Startup Clinic will allow entrepreneurs to meet one on one with investors and prominent entrepreneurs to receive feedback on their startup and pitch. Access to signups for Startup Clinic will emailed with your eventbrite confirmation. First Come, First Served.

Pitch Competition. The pitch competition is an opporunity for you to pitch your company to investors and the general public. Five companies will be chosen to pitch their idea live during the conference.

Who should attend? Anyone working in technology, from early-stage startup to corporate to investments. Anyone who is thinking about starting a startup, or has a general interest in technology and innovation. This includes but is not limited to: engineers, entrepreneurs, designers, product managers, marketers, business development, and investors.


For more information, visit http://www.blackfoundersconference.com

column14:
DC Tech + SXSW


Each year hundreds of DC area tech enthusiasts migrate to Austin for SXSW Interactive. And each year, someone organizes an informal DC Tech meetup so everyone can, well, get together in Austin.

This year the venue and drinks are on us!

Tech Cocktail is excited to host the DC Tech Meetup @ SXSW, sponsored by the Washington, DC Economic Partnership with support by the DC Government.



When: Saturday, March 9th, 2011 at 2:00pm - 4:00pm


Where: The Stage on Sixth, 508 East 6th Street, Austin, TX


Price: Free - please RSVP now (must be 21+ years old to drink)



Thank you to the Washington, DC Economic Partnership for supporting this event!


AND LATER IN THE EVENING....

Come back later in the evening for our Startup Celebration! RSVP Now!

Chances are, if you've been to SXSW in years' past, you're familiar with how we roll. In case you missed the previous festivities, check these links from SXSW 2012, SXSW 2011 and SXSW 2010.

Showcase Your Startup
Want to showcase your startup in front of hundreds of fellow technology enthusiasts, investors, and high profile media? You can - simply fill out the application here.


Interested in Sponsoring?
Sponsorship opportunities are available for all the various activities. If you are interested contact us here and we’ll circle back with the SXSW information.

Evening Mixer Event details:

When: Saturday, March 9th, 2011 at 6:00 p.m. till the cows come home

Where: The Stage on Sixth, 508 East 6th Street, Austin, TX

What: A cocktail of tech and startup enthusiasts

Price: Free with a SXSW badge (must be 21+ years old to enter)

***RSVP does not guarantee entrance. First come first serve.

Tech Cocktail (http://tech.co) is a media company that covers the latest tech innovations across the globe. Tech Cocktail has been hosting mixer events and writing about technology start-ups and entrepreneurs across the country with the focus of helping to amplify the local technology signal since 2006. We have hosted large events in Chicago, D.C., NY, San Francisco, Boston, Boulder, San Diego, Detroit, Boise, Austin, Barcelona and more. Read more about Tech Cocktail.

column2: LoudDoor presents with Dighu OMMA Social (Platinum / Gold / Interactive Badges)
column6: 1 AT&T Center Parkway, San Antonio, TX, 78219
column13: Register HERE - Free with Platinum, Gold or Interactive Badge & Registration|Your Brand Is Social. Now What?OMMA Social at SXSW is a focused, half-day show incorporated into SXSW Interactive. It is designed to guide marketers and agency execs through the terrain of social media and how it relates to their brands and Web presence. This special edition aims to go beyond what might be called Social Marketing 1.0, by demonstrating, through keynotes, panels and case studies, how to engage social consumers beyond “Likes”, follows and simply buying ads on social platforms. |How can marketers use social to motivate audiences? Improve targeting using new tools such as Facebook Graph Search? How should social engagement be measured? Is it possible to integrate campaigns across differing social media channels? And can marketers and agencies combine paid and earned media into provocative social campaigns? column14:
Register HERE - Free with Platinum, Gold or Interactive Badge & Registration

Your Brand Is Social. Now What?

OMMA Social at SXSW is a focused, half-day show incorporated into SXSW Interactive. It is designed to guide marketers and agency execs through the terrain of social media and how it relates to their brands and Web presence. This special edition aims to go beyond what might be called Social Marketing 1.0, by demonstrating, through keynotes, panels and case studies, how to engage social consumers beyond “Likes”, follows and simply buying ads on social platforms.

How can marketers use social to motivate audiences? Improve targeting using new tools such as Facebook Graph Search? How should social engagement be measured? Is it possible to integrate campaigns across differing social media channels? And can marketers and agencies combine paid and earned media into provocative social campaigns? OMMA Social at SXSW will grapple with those issues, and many more.


What To Expect

* Hear from the top names in social media as they share the secrets of connecting with consumers using
social media and marketing.

* Gain indispensable knowledge and insight into emerging social media and trends within the

* Discover today’s best practices for social marketing, going beyond the simple accumulation of brand
followers.

* Explore how individual brands are using social media through two focused case studies on state-of-the-art
social marketing.

* Learn about the newest social data tools, and how they can be used to reach customers.


Video from the last OMMA Social

column2: Official SXSW Geospatial Meetup 2013 (Badges Only)
column13: Join us for the Official SXSW 2013 Geospatial Meetup. LBS, GIS, SoLoMo and every other trade acronym (Good & Bad) for ambient technologies are on the rise and are here to stay. What are location-based services, geospatial information services, social-local-mobile, and ambient and why do we need to care? To learn how to apply and utilize these innovative technologies in the real world, engage users, and where the industry and technology is heading, come meet with experts ranging from F500 geospatial experts to innovative startup founders all looking to crack the code. Take this opportunity to network with like-minded individuals who are on the forefront of this rapidly evolving field within the mobile sector. We know that 11am after a fun-filled night at SXSW may sound early, but don't worry, we're tapping into our Texas roots and will have a Bloody Mary Bar plus breakfast tacos aplenty. Can't wait to see you at the Official SXSW Geospatial Meetup 2013! Must have a SXSW badge or day pass to attend. |More information here: http://schedule.sxsw.com/2013/events/event_IAP993349

column14:
HEAR THERE. EVERYWHERE.
The 6th Annual Dart Music International House

Since 2008 DMI has helped Austin "Hear There. Everywhere." by presenting unprecedented international cultural events in Austin during the big festival week. Some of the highlights have included historic events like "Music From Space" (an exclusive video from the International Space Station), "6 Bands 6 Continents" (back-to-back performances by artists from every inhabited continent), and "Taquacore + i:Made in Israel + ATX Hip Hop" (Iranian, Israeli, and Austin artists performing together).


This year is going to add to that legacy in an informal, "happy hour" setting. From Tuesday, March 12 through Friday, March 15, in between the music panels / day parties and the nightly showcases, DMI will be producing the 6th Annual Dart Music International Houseevent in downtown Austin. This is your opportunity of a lifetime to experience global culture in an informal setting. We hope to see you there!

column2: IEEE Standards Association presents: Digital Telepathy: When Every Thing Connects
column13: Once upon a time, our phone, the fridge and TV were distinct devices, manufactured in distinctly different environments. Not anymore. Today, our devices share technologies in an unprecedented manner. We can use our phone to watch on-demand programming.|When the power goes out, we may get a text notification from our fridge. Questions AnsweredIn real terms, what is the "Internet of Things" and is it just a buzzword?What are the big social changes we might predict as millions of users effectively imprint the Internet onto our physical environments?We can all see that more of our devices, tools and toys are becoming connected in ways we never imagined even 5 years ago. What benefits can connectivity and convergence bring to society and culture? How can these benefits support support developing countries and building a more sustainable world?As we move towards a world of very realistic interaction with physically remote experiences, what are the implications on our personal relationships, geography, careers, privacy and personal identity?Even with all this convergence and connection, there are moments where I want to be by myself, or just share with a couple of people. If I don’t want others to know what I am doing and where I am, how can I ensure the privacy and proper partitioning of my information? Will sharing be "the norm" or my choice?|Presented by:|Joe Weinman, Sr VP, Telx |Oleg Logvinov, Dir Market Dev Industrial & Power Conversion Division, STMicroelectronicsWael Diab, Sr Technical Dir, BroadcomKaren Bartleson, Sr. Director, Community Marketing, Synosys and IEEE-SA President|Hashtags:|#sxsw #DigTel|via Eventbrite
column14:
Once upon a time, our phone, the fridge and TV were distinct devices, manufactured in distinctly different environments. Not anymore. Today, our devices share technologies in an unprecedented manner. We can use our phone to watch on-demand programming.


When the power goes out, we may get a text notification from our fridge. If you're higher tech, the grocery list can transfer easily through your wireless network from your Smart Fridge to any device. Convergence and interconnection are the new name of the game, and along with apps and wireless networking, several revolutionary interconnection technologies will soon change every detail of our lives - forever.


This is the Internet of Things - a future where people and objects communicate in unprecedented ways. In this panel we'll explore the dynamics of interconnection and convergence and address the need for a more interdisciplinary approach to design, engineering, development, communication and privacy.

Questions Answered

  • In real terms, what is the "Internet of Things" and is it just a buzzword?
  • What are the big social changes we might predict as millions of users effectively imprint the Internet onto our physical environments?
  • We can all see that more of our devices, tools and toys are becoming connected in ways we never imagined even 5 years ago. What benefits can connectivity and convergence bring to society and culture? How can these benefits support support developing countries and building a more sustainable world?
  • As we move towards a world of very realistic interaction with physically remote experiences, what are the implications on our personal relationships, geography, careers, privacy and personal identity?
  • Even with all this convergence and connection, there are moments where I want to be by myself, or just share with a couple of people. If I don’t want others to know what I am doing and where I am, how can I ensure the privacy and proper partitioning of my information? Will sharing be "the norm" or my choice?


Presented by:


  • Joe Weinman, Sr VP, Telx
  • Oleg Logvinov, Dir Market Dev Industrial & Power Conversion Division, STMicroelectronics
  • Wael Diab, Sr Technical Dir, Broadcom
  • Karen Bartleson, Sr. Director, Community Marketing, Synosys and IEEE-SA President

column14:
HEAR THERE. EVERYWHERE.
The 6th Annual Dart Music International House

Since 2008 DMI has helped Austin "Hear There. Everywhere." by presenting unprecedented international cultural events in Austin during the big festival week. Some of the highlights have included historic events like "Music From Space" (an exclusive video from the International Space Station), "6 Bands 6 Continents" (back-to-back performances by artists from every inhabited continent), and "Taquacore + i:Made in Israel + ATX Hip Hop" (Iranian, Israeli, and Austin artists performing together).


This year is going to add to that legacy in an informal, "happy hour" setting. From Tuesday, March 12 through Friday, March 15, in between the music panels / day parties and the nightly showcases, DMI will be producing the 6th Annual Dart Music International Houseevent in downtown Austin. This is your opportunity of a lifetime to experience global culture in an informal setting. We hope to see you there!


WHEN: Tuesday, March 12 through Friday, March 15, 2013; 5:00-8:00PM Daily


WHERE: Mark McCrimmon Law Office, 704 West 9th Street, Austin TX 78701 (Map)


WHAT: Music & culture with Artists from around the world - Every Inhabited Continent


WHO: Presented by Dart Music International with complimentary food and drinks from The Peached Tortilla, Austin Beerworks, and more.

column2: IEEE Standards Association presents: Omnipresent: When Virtual Meets Reality
column13: When the “virtual overlay” meets everyday life, everything changes, from the way we shop to the way we interact with the world around us. Today, augmented reality is moving beyond the virtual dimension to enhance real world experiences, meshing with and revolutionizing interactive training, real-world simulation, design, architecture, manufacturing, medicine and more. This panel explores new advancements in Virtual / Augmented Reality and the short and long-term impacts AR may carry. We'll also explore the not-so-distant future, highlighting the creative opportunities that exist for the development of new AR solutions, standards and enabling technologies. Questions AnsweredWhat are the most promising developments in computer vision that could take Augmented Reality (AR) to the next level or beyond?Having to use a phone or tablet for Augmented Reality limits the technology's vast potential. So, how will we be "seeing" AR in ten years?What kind of common infrastructure is needed to tie together the augmented world?Are synthetic and mixed environments the universal "next-generation interface"?What the heck is a spime and why should I care? What other new terminology should I be on the lookout for as reality shifts?|Presented by:|BC "Heavy" Biermann, Founder, The Heavy Projects Blair MacIntyre, Assoc Professor, Georgia Institute of TechnologyChristine Perey, Spime Wrangler, Perey Research & ConsultingJay Iorio, Technology Strategist, IEEE|Hashtags:|#sxsw #omnipres|View the event in the Official SXSW schedule
column14:
When the “virtual overlay” meets everyday life, everything changes, from the way we shop to the way we interact with the world around us. Today, augmented reality is moving beyond the virtual dimension to enhance real world experiences, meshing with and revolutionizing interactive training, real-world simulation, design, architecture, manufacturing, medicine and more. This panel explores new advancements in Virtual / Augmented Reality and the short and long-term impacts AR may carry. We'll also explore the not-so-distant future, highlighting the creative opportunities that exist for the development of new AR solutions, standards and enabling technologies.

Questions Answered

  • What are the most promising developments in computer vision that could take Augmented Reality (AR) to the next level or beyond?
  • Having to use a phone or tablet for Augmented Reality limits the technology's vast potential. So, how will we be "seeing" AR in ten years?
  • What kind of common infrastructure is needed to tie together the augmented world?
  • Are synthetic and mixed environments the universal "next-generation interface"?
  • What the heck is a spime and why should I care? What other new terminology should I be on the lookout for as reality shifts?


Presented by:

  • BC "Heavy" Biermann, Founder, The Heavy Projects
  • Blair MacIntyre, Assoc Professor, Georgia Institute of Technology
  • Christine Perey, Spime Wrangler, Perey Research & Consulting
  • Jay Iorio, Technology Strategist, IEEE



Hashtags:

#sxsw #omnipres

column2: Brooklyn Brewery presents NY Night Train Soul Clap & Dance Off
column13: DANCE CONTEST|Fri, March 8th|9:00pm - 11:30pm|755 Springdale Rd, Austin, TX|DJ Mr. Jonathan Toubin's Soul Clap and Dance-Off is North America's most popular soul party - by far playing to more people in more places and generating more capital than any of its contemporaries. Founded in New York City the concept is simple-all night dancing to the wild soul 45s of subterranean superstar DJ Mr. Jonathan Toubin and, in the middle, a $100 dance contest judged by a community panel. Cash is great. But so is a trip to Brooklyn for the dance-off championship at Brooklyn Bowl. Get your moves down cause the fine folks from Tumblr and Imgur will be judging the hell out of you from their perch on the dance contest panel.|Recession-friendly mass entertainment with a universally cheap door price, the dance party/spectacle not only sells beyond capacity at home, but has brought its excitement to domestic markets all the way from Portland, Oregon to Portland, Maine and internationally from Tel Aviv to Mexico City-including monthly residencies in New York, Chicago, LA, San Francisco, Oakland, and PDX. The Dance-Off portion features judges from every edge of music and culture from classic subcultural icons like Mike Watt and Jello Biafra, to rock stars Andrew Van Wyngarden (MGMT) and Nick Zinner (Yeah Yeah Yeahs), to interesting cultural figures like Karla LaVey (Satanic Priestess) and Matt Gonzalez (Green Party Vice Presidential Candidate) to your favorite neighborhood heroes. |Catch The Soul Clap!|via Brooklyn Brewery Mash
column14:
DANCE CONTEST



Fri, March 8th
9:00pm - 11:30pm
755 Springdale Rd, Austin, TX


DJ Mr. Jonathan Toubin's Soul Clap and Dance-Off is North America's most popular soul party - by far playing to more people in more places and generating more capital than any of its contemporaries. Founded in New York City the concept is simple-all night dancing to the wild soul 45s of subterranean superstar DJ Mr. Jonathan Toubin and, in the middle, a $100 dance contest judged by a community panel. Cash is great. But so is a trip to Brooklyn for the dance-off championship at Brooklyn Bowl. Get your moves down cause the fine folks from Tumblr and Imgur will be judging the hell out of you from their perch on the dance contest panel.



Recession-friendly mass entertainment with a universally cheap door price, the dance party/spectacle not only sells beyond capacity at home, but has brought its excitement to domestic markets all the way from Portland, Oregon to Portland, Maine and internationally from Tel Aviv to Mexico City-including monthly residencies in New York, Chicago, LA, San Francisco, Oakland, and PDX. The Dance-Off portion features judges from every edge of music and culture from classic subcultural icons like Mike Watt and Jello Biafra, to rock stars Andrew Van Wyngarden (MGMT) and Nick Zinner (Yeah Yeah Yeahs), to interesting cultural figures like Karla LaVey (Satanic Priestess) and Matt Gonzalez (Green Party Vice Presidential Candidate) to your favorite neighborhood heroes.



Catch The Soul Clap!


via Brooklyn Brewery Mash

The protocol serves as a “message bus” for social applications, enabling apps developed by disparate vendors to communicate with each other in real-time, resulting in a seamless, unified user experience. column14:

Echo and Janrain invite you to kick off SX2013 Interactive with a fun and informative networking event celebrating the incredible recent success of Backplane Protocol. What is Backplane Protocol? If you have to ask, you HAVE to be here! We'll serve you some tasty microbrews, deliver the inside skinny and give you ample time to chat with industry peers and big brands on what you've been missing so far. So why not stop by, grab a beer and learn something you can take back to your boss to help justify your Southby attendance!


Schedule:

2:30pm - 2:45pm Industry Meet-and-Greet & Beer Tasting
2:45pm - 3:00pm Introduction to Backplane Protocol
Khris Loux, Co-founder and CEO, Echo
3:00pm - 3:30pm Overview of the Technical Specification
3:30pm - 4:00pm Case Study: Universal Music Group Uses Backplane Protocol to Integrate
Best of Breed Apps, Reducing Cost and Time-to-Market
Lee Hammond, VP of Digital, Interscope Geffen A&M
4:00pm - 4:30pm Networking with App Developers and Brands

About Backplane Protocol


Backplane Protocol solves a key interoperability problem that emerged when brands started integrating multiple 3rd party web applications like real-time commenting, social login and game mechanics into their sites in order to provide web visitors with a modern, social user experience. The protocol serves as a “message bus” for social applications, enabling apps developed by disparate vendors to communicate with each other in real-time, resulting in a seamless, unified user experience. In July 2012, the OpenID Foundation launched Backplane Protocol Working Group to solicit input from the global OpenID community on the standard. Backplane Protocol is currently in use by some of the largest media companies in the world, including ABC, ESPN, NBC Universal, Universal Music Group and WWE. App providers who support Backplane Protocol include 500 Friends, Arktan, Badgeville, BigDoor, CalmSea, Caterva, Chute, Disqus, Echo, Envolve, Janrain, JetJaw, Livefyre, Marketo, Realtidbits, Stocial, Tokbox, TurnTo, Umbel and Viafora.


via Eventbrite

2nd Annual Techweek Chicago Party @ SXSWi

Less than 4 months until Techweek Chicago! Join us at Copa Lounge to celebrate the midway mark of SXSW interactive and the count down to our 3rd annual Chicago conference. REGISTER HERE

2013 Open Web SXSW Pool Party

With so many proponents of the Open Web in one place during SXSW, it only makes sense to have an event celebrating our achievements and to get to know one another beyond our online personas. That's what the Open Web Pool Party at SXSW is all about!

Party Details

  • A 14-Time Flare Bartending Champion Serving Up Libations

  • DJ Johnny Bravo Providing Proper Party Music

  • Local Photographer Extraordinaire Annie Ray Capturing The Event

  • Pool Party-Inspired Bites by A Local Food Vendor

And what party would be complete without door prizes?

This year, in addition to our usual cache of electronic devices we tend to hand out, we're sending you to an actual pool...in Puerto Vallarta.


One lucky attendee will go home with with a 5 day/4 night all inclusive resort package to a fancy place in Puerto Vallarta, Mexico.
